{E71: King's Indian: 4 e4 d6 5 h3} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. h3 O-O 6. Be3 Nc6 7. d5 Ne5 8. Qc2 e6 {White is slightly better.} 9. f4 Ned7 10. dxe6 $1 {&Bianco is more active.} fxe6 11. g4 {Against Nh5} Qe7 $146 (11... b6 12. O-O-O Bb7 13. Bg2 Nc5 14. Nge2 {B6-6... Nc6 and 7... Ne5 #1}) 12. Nge2 Nb6 {[#]} 13. b3 $1 d5 14. e5 {Black is on the road to losing.} Nfd7 15. Bg2 Nxe5 {[%eval 128,19]} 16. fxe5 $16 Qh4+ 17. Kd2 Bh6 18. Qd3 (18. cxd5 $6 Bxe3+ 19. Kxe3 Qf2+ 20. Kd2 Qxg2 $11) 18... dxc4 {[#]} 19. Qe4 Nd5 {[%eval 243,21]} (19... Bd7 $142 {[%eval 164,18]} 20. g5 Bxg5 21. Qxh4 Bxh4 22. Bxb7 Rad8) 20. Nxd5 $18 exd5 21. Qd4 Be6 {[%eval 218,20]} (21... Bxe3+ $142 {[%eval 181,19]} 22. Qxe3 Be6) 22. g5 Bxg5 {Threatens to win with ...Qxd4+.} 23. Qxh4 {The board is on fire.} Bxh4 24. Nd4 Rfe8 25. bxc4 dxc4 26. Bxb7 (26. Nxe6 Rxe6 27. Kc3 (27. Bxb7 Rd8+ 28. Kc3 Rd3+ 29. Kxc4 Rxe3 $14) 27... Rxe5) 26... Rad8 {Strongly threatening ...c5.} 27. Ke2 Bd5 28. Bxd5+ Rxd5 29. Nf3 Bg3 30. Rhd1 (30. Bxa7 Bxe5 31. Nxe5 Rexe5+ 32. Kf2 Rf5+ 33. Kg3 Rg5+ 34. Kf4 Rgf5+ 35. Kg4 Rg5+ 36. Kf4 Rgf5+ 37. Kg4 Rg5+ 38. Kf3 Rgf5+ 39. Ke4 Rfe5+ 40. Kf4 Rf5+ $11) 30... Bxe5 31. Rxd5 Bxa1 32. Rc5 Rb8 33. a4 (33. Rxc4 $6 Rb2+ 34. Kd3 Rxa2 35. Rxc7 a5 36. Rc8+ Kg7 $18) 33... Rb4 34. a5 (34. Rxc7 a5 35. Rc8+ Kg7) 34... a6 35. Nd2 ({Resist} 35. Rxc7 Ra4 36. Bd2 Bf6 $18) 35... c3 36. Nc4 ({Not} 36. Rxc7 cxd2 37. Rc6 Rb3 38. Bxd2 Rxh3 $11) 36... Rb2+ 37. Kd3 Rh2 38. Rc6 c2 39. Rxa6 c5 40. Ra8+ Kf7 41. a6 Bd4 {And now ...Bxe3 would win.} 42. Bd2 c1=Q 43. Bxc1 Rxh3+ 44. Be3 Bxe3 45. Nxe3 c4+ 46. Kxc4 Rxe3 {KR-KR} 47. a7 ({Less strong is} 47. Ra7+ Kf6 $16) 47... Re7 48. Rh8 Rc7+ 49. Kd4 Rd7+ 50. Ke4 Re7+ 51. Kf3 $146 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.03 (flawless) /Black=0.30} 1-0


