ng's position.}) 10. f4 {White's control of the centre promises an edge.} Bg6 11. O-O $1 {Threatening 12 f5, which prompts Black to offer trades on the e4-square. Threatening 12 f5, which prompts Black to offer trades on the e4-square. D Cummings,MH: 'Threatening 12 f5, which prompts Black to offer trades on the e4-square. David Cummings,MH: '!''} Be4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 dxe4 14. Qb3 {How should Black deal with the double attack on f7 and b7?} Bxe5 $6 {[%eval 159,24] Black maintains the material balance, but this is objectively dubious. Instead:} (14... O-O $14 {[%eval 61,22] D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '''} 15. Qxb7 Nb6 {[#] [#] D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '[#]''} 16. Qxc6 {[%eval 47,19] sheds two pawns, but after} (16. Be3 $1 $16 {[%eval 89,19] D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH'}) 16... Bxe5 $14 {D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '''} 17. dxe5 {[%cal Oc1e3] Black must now prevent Bc1-e3! Black must now prevent Bc1-e3! D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: ' Black must now prevent Bc1-e3!''} Qd4+ 18. e3 $1 {[%cal Re3d4] D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '!''} Qd3 {Black has decent compensation due to White's lack of development.}) 15. dxe5 $146 {The correct recapture. The correct recapture. D Cummings,MH: 'The correct recapture. David Cummings,MH: 'N''} (15. fxe5 $6 {[%eval 40,19] 15.d4xe5 1.53 15.d4xe5 1.53 D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '?!' '15.d4xe5 1.53''} O-O $14 {D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH: '''} 16. Qxb7 Nb6 17. Be3 (17. e3 {D Cummings,MH: 'David Cummings,MH'} Qd5 (17... Qg5 18. Kg2 Nd5 19. Qxc6 Rac8 20. Qxd5 Rc2+ 21. Rf2 Rxf2+ 22. Kxf2 Qf5+ 23. Ke1 Rc8 24. Qb7 h5 25. Bd2 Qxh3 26. Qxe4 Qxg3+ 27. Ke2 h4 28. Rf1 h3 29. e6 f6 30. Qf3 Qg6 31. Qf5 Qg2+ 32. Rf2 {1-0 Yu,Y (2729)-Indjic,A (2641) Titled Tuesday intern op 14th Feb Late Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (6) 1-0 Yu,Y (2729)-Indjic,A (2641) Titled Tuesday intern op 14th Feb Late Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (6) D Cummings,MH: '1-0 Yu,Y (2729)-Indjic,A (2641) Titled Tuesday intern op 14th