{C67: Ruy Lopez: Berlin Defence: 4 0-0 Nxe4} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. Re1 Nd6 6. Nxe5 Be7 7. Bf1 Nxe5 8. Rxe5 O-O 9. d4 Bf6 10. Re1 Re8 {The main line 10...Re8 scores better than 10...Nf5. Die Hauptvariante 10...Te8 punktet besser als 10...Sf5.} 11. Bf4 Rxe1 12. Qxe1 Ne8 {The position is equal.} 13. Nc3 {[%eval -9,20]} (13. Bd3 $14 {[%eval 34,20]}) 13... Bxd4 $11 14. Nd5 d6 $1 15. Bg5 f6 $1 16. Bh4 (16. Bc4 Kh8 17. Be3 Bxb2 18. Rb1 Be5 19. f4 c6 20. Bd3 cxd5 21. Qh4 h6 22. fxe5 dxe5 23. Bg6 Kg8 24. Bxh6 gxh6 25. Qxh6 Qe7 26. Rb3 Bg4 27. Qh4 {Dominguez Perez,L (2754)-Aronian,L (2775) Saint Louis (blitz) 154/ (125) 2022 [Perunovic,Milos]}) 16... Bxb2 {[%eval -6,21]} (16... g5 $15 {[%eval -39,21] is more appropriate.} 17. Ne7+ Kh8 18. Nxc8 Rxc8) ({RR} 16... g5 17. Qe4 Bxb2 18. Rb1 Be5 19. f4 gxh4 20. fxe5 dxe5 21. Bc4 Be6 22. Rxb7 Kh8 23. Bd3 Bg8 24. Nxc7 Nd6 25. Qxh4 Nxb7 26. Nxa8 Nc5 27. Bf5 e4 28. h3 Qd4+ 29. Kh1 Qa1+ {0-1 (29) Caruana,F (2820)-So,W (2770) Paris 2021}) ({RR} 16... g5 17. Qe4 Bxb2 18. Re1 Be5 19. f4 gxh4 20. fxe5 dxe5 21. Bd3 Bf5 22. Qxf5 Qxd5 23. Qxh7+ Kf8 24. Qh6+ Ke7 25. Qh7+ Kf8 26. Qh6+ Ke7 27. Qh7+ Kf8 28. Qh6+ Ke7 {½-½ (28) Bruzon Batista,L (2559)-Quesada Perez,Y (2566) Saint Louis 2025}) ({RR} 16... g5 17. Qe4 Bxb2 18. Re1 Be5 19. f4 gxh4 20. fxe5 dxe5 21. Bd3 Bf5 22. Qxf5 Qxd5 23. Qxh7+ Kf8 24. Qh6+ Ke7 25. Qh7+ Kf8 26. Qh6+ Ke7 27. Qh7+ Kf8 28. Qh6+ {½-½ (28) Vachier Lagrave,M (2734)-Firouzja,A (2777) Saint Louis 2023}) 17. Rb1 Be5 {...c7-c6 is the strong threat.} 18. f4 $1 Be6 $146 {[%eval 107,22] [#]} (18... Bd4+ 19. Kh1 Kh8 20. Bd3 c6 21. Ne7 d5 22. Qe2 h6 23. Ng6+ Kg8 24. Rxb7 Nd6 25. Ne7+ Kf8 26. Ng6+ Kg8 27. Ne7+ Kf8 28. Nxc6 Qe8 29. Qxe8+ Nxe8 30. Rb5 Be3 31. Be1 Nc7 32. Rb4 Bd7 33. Rb7 {Hetenyi,G (2581)-7.Bg2 Nc6 8.h3 Qc7 (2519) Pori Barcares 2023 Steinitz/Blackburne [John Watson] 1-0 (69)}) ({Vorgänger:} 18... c6 19. fxe5 cxd5 20. exf6 Nxf6 21. Bd3 Bd7 22. Qg3 Bc6 23. Bf5 (23. Rf1 Qb6+ 24. Kh1 Ne4 25. Qf4 h6 26. Qf7+ Kh8 27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. Bf6 Rg8 29. Qg6 Qe3 30. Bxg7+ {1-0 (30) Gazi,M (2682)-8... Nbd7 (2666) Moscow 2019 CBM 103 ext [Grob NZZ-3 p17 FSZ#721]}) (23. Bg5 a6 24. Rf1 Qb6+ {Huschenbeth,N (2605)-Navara,D (2689) FIDE Grand Swiss 2023 (1) 1-0}) 23... Kh8 24. Qh3 Qe7 25. Bxh7 {Muzychuk,M (2560)-Lagno,K (2559) Astana 2019 Chess Informant 141 [Tadic,Branko]}) ({RR} 18... c6 19. fxe5 cxd5 20. exf6 Nxf6 21. Bd3 Bd7 22. Qg3 Bc6 23. Rf1 Qb6+ 24. Kh1 Ne4 25. Qf4 h6 26. Qf7+ Kh8 27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. Bf6 Rg8 29. Qg6 Qe3 30. Bxg7+ {1-0 (30) Firouzja,A (2682)-Sevian,S (2666) Chess.com INT 2019}) ({RR} 18... c6 19. fxe5 cxd5 20. exf6 Nxf6 21. Bd3 Bd7 22. h3 b5 23. Bxb5 Qe8 24. Qxe8+ Bxe8 25. Ba6 Bg6 26. Bxf6 gxf6 27. Bb7 Re8 28. Bxd5+ Bf7 29. Bxf7+ Kxf7 30. Rb7+ Kg6 31. Rxa7 Rc8 32. Rd7 Rxc2 33. Rxd6 {Karjakin,S (2781)-Anand,V (2786) Stavanger 2017 ½-½ (33)}) 19. Bc4 $1 $16 {White has strong compensation.} Bd4+ 20. Kh1 Bf7 21. Qe4 Bc5 {[#]} 22. Ne7+ $1 Kf8 {[#]} 23. Qxh7 $1 {Intending Qh7-g8+! and mate. &Bianco is much more active. The black rooks are badly placed.} Bxc4 24. Re1 $40 {Qh7-h8+ would kill now. White is out for blood.} Qxe7 25. Rxe7 Kxe7 26. Qe4+ Be6 {aiming for ...d6-d5.} 27. f5 {Pin} Rd8 28. g4 (28. fxe6 $6 c6 $14) 28... c6 $2 {[%eval 343,26] Loses the game.} 29. g5 $18 {Really sharp!} ({Inferior is} 29. fxe6 d5 30. Qf5 g5 $14) (29. Qxe6+ Kf8 $16) 29... Kf8 (29... Nc7 $2 30. gxf6+ gxf6 31. fxe6 $18) 30. fxe6 ({Weaker is} 30. Qxe6 Nc7 31. Qb3 fxg5 $18) 30... Ke7 31. gxf6+ gxf6 {[%eval 472,24]} (31... Nxf6 {[%eval 334,27] was called for.} 32. Qg4 (32. Qg6 Kxe6 33. Qxg7 Bd4 $16) 32... g5 33. Bxg5 Rf8) 32. Qg4 {White threatens Qg4-g8 and mate.} d5 {[%eval 698,21]} (32... Rc8 $142 {[%eval 465,24]} 33. Qg6 Rc7 34. Qf7+ Kd8 35. Bxf6+ Nxf6 36. Qxf6+ Re7) 33. Qg8 {White wants to mate with Qg8-f7+.} Bd4 34. Bg3 Be5 35. Bxe5 fxe5 {Endgame KQ-KRN} 36. h4 e4 37. h5 d4 38. Qf7+ Kd6 39. e7 {White is clearly winning.} Rc8 40. Qf4+ Kxe7 41. Qxe4+ Kd7 42. Qxd4+ Nd6 43. h6 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.16 (very precise) /Black=0.33} 1-0


