{A29: English Opening: Four Knights Variation with 4 g3} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 (4. a3 g6 5. g3 Bg7 (5... d5 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. O-O Nxc3 9. dxc3 O-O 10. Bg5 Qxd1 11. Rfxd1 h6 12. Be3 a5 13. Bc5 Re8 14. e4 a4 15. Bf1 Bg4 16. Kg2 Na5 17. Be3 c6 18. h3 Be6 19. Bb6 Nc4 20. Bxc4 {½-½ Locci,D-Romanishin,O Bratto op 2009 (1)}) 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O d5 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Nxe5 Nxc3 10. Nxc6 Nxe2+ 11. Qxe2 bxc6 12. Bxc6 Rb8 13. d3 Bh3 14. Re1 Rb6 15. Qc2 Be6 16. Be4 Qd7 17. Qc5 Bd4 18. Qa5 Rb5 {½-½ Dragon Variation,Y (2550)-Stamnov,A (2561) USSR 45/(175) 1988 (3)}) 4... Bb4 $146 (4... d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 Nb6 7. d3 Be7 8. Be3 O-O 9. Rc1 f5 10. Na4 e4 11. Qb3+ Kh8 12. dxe4 fxe4 13. Nd2 Nd4 14. Qd1 Nf5 {A 29/15  2000}) (4... g6 5. Bg2 Bg7 6. O-O O-O 7. d3 d6 8. b3 Re8 9. Re1 h6 10. Bb2 Be6 11. Rc1 Qd7 12. a3 a5 13. Nb5 Rac8 14. e4 Bh3 15. d4 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 exd4 17. Nbxd4 Nxe4 {0-1 Livanez-Litvin,A (2425) (m/1) 96/87 Khanty Mansiysk 2005}) 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O e4 7. Ng5 Bxc3 8. bxc3 Re8 9. f3 exf3 10. Nxf3 d5 ({RR} 10... Qe7 11. e3 Ne5 12. Nxe5 Qxe5 13. Rb1 Rb8 14. Rb5 Qe7 15. d3 d6 16. e4 Bg4 17. Bf3 Bh3 18. Bg2 Bg4 19. Bf3 Bh3 20. Bg2 {½-½ (20) Aronian,L (2780)-Anand,V (2804) Stavanger 2015}) 11. d4 $1 h6 $1 {[%mdl 4] Prevents Bc1-g5. now scores much better than the old 11...Ne4. punktet besser als das ältere 11...Se4.} ({RR} 11... dxc4 12. Bg5 Bg4 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Ne5 Qg5 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Nxf7 Qe3+ 17. Rf2 Rf8 18. Qf1 Rxf7 {0-1 (18) Matlak,O (2235)-Altini,N (2350) Chess.com INT 2025}) 12. cxd5 ({RR} 12. Qc2 dxc4 13. Bf4 Bg4 14. Rae1 Bh5 15. Nh4 g5 16. Nf5 gxf4 17. Nxh6+ Kf8 18. Rxf4 Bg6 19. Qd2 Nd5 20. Bxd5 Qxd5 21. e4 Qd7 22. Ref1 Nd8 23. d5 Rxe4 24. Rf6 Ke8 25. Qg5 Qe7 26. Rxg6 fxg6 {Svidler,P (2683)-Vidit,S (2731) Nagpur 2023 0-1 (33)}) 12... Qxd5 {The position is equal.} 13. Ne5 $146 {was the old line (13.Nh4). war die alte Variante (13.Sh4).} ({RR} 13. Bf4 Qc4 14. Qd3 Qxd3 15. exd3 Nd5 16. Bd2 Bg4 17. Ne5 Nxe5 18. Bxd5 c6 19. Be4 f5 20. dxe5 fxe4 21. d4 Be6 22. Rf4 Bd5 23. a4 Rf8 24. a5 g5 25. Rxf8+ {½-½ (25) Langrock,H (2383)-Pacher,M (2358) Olomouc 2009}) ({RR} 13. e3 Bf5 14. Nd2 Qd7 15. Nb3 Ne4 16. c4 b6 17. Rf4 Rad8 18. Qf1 Bg6 19. Ba3 Na5 20. Bb4 Nxb3 21. axb3 c5 22. Bxe4 Rxe4 23. Rxe4 Bxe4 24. Bc3 Bc2 25. b4 cxb4 26. Bxb4 a5 27. Bc3 Rc8 {Aronian,L (2777)-Adams,M (2738) Baden-Baden 2015 ½-½ (56)}) 13... Qe6 14. Bf4 $146 ({Vorgänger:} 14. Nd3 Qxe2 15. Bxh6 Qxd1 16. Raxd1 Bg4 17. Rd2 Be2 18. Rxf6 gxf6 19. Nc5 Bc4 {White must now prevent ...Re8-e1+.} 20. Nxb7 {½-½ Morley,P (2365)-Zemlyanov,S (2389) LAT jub25/B email 2017}) 14... Nxe5 15. dxe5 Ng4 16. Bd5 {[%eval -131,22] [#]} (16. Qd4 $1 $11 {[%eval -29,20]}) 16... Qb6+ {[%eval -43,19]} ({Black should try} 16... Qg6 $1 $17 {[%eval -131,22][%cal Og6h5] Strongly threatening ...Qg6-h5!} 17. Bg2 Bf5 (17... Nxe5 18. Bxe5 Rxe5 19. Qd8+ Kh7 20. Qxc7 $14)) 17. Qd4 $15 Be6 ({Of course not} 17... Nxe5 18. Bxe5 Rxe5 19. Bxf7+ Kh8 20. Rf2 $11) 18. Qxb6 cxb6 {[%eval -14,23]} (18... axb6 $17 {[%eval -89,26]} 19. Bxb7 Ra5 (19... Rxa2 20. h3 $16)) 19. Bxb7 $11 {This pair of bishops is nice.} Rab8 20. Ba6 {aiming for h2-h3.} g5 21. Bc1 Nxe5 {next ...Be6-c4 is good for Black.} 22. h4 Bh3 23. Rd1 f6 24. hxg5 hxg5 25. a4 Be6 26. Bb5 Rec8 27. Rd6 Kf7 28. a5 Rc5 29. axb6 $2 {[%eval -269,23] This move loses the game for White.} (29. Bd3 $1 $15 {[%eval -63,20]}) 29... Rxb5 $19 (29... axb6 30. Ra7+ Kg6 31. Re7 $11) 30. Rxa7+ {[%eval -361,21] [#]} (30. bxa7 {[%eval -239,19] was forced.} Ra8 31. Kf1) 30... Kg6 $1 31. Rxe6 Rb1 $1 ({And not} 31... R5xb6 32. Rxb6 Rxb6 33. Kf2 $11) 32. Kg2 Rxc1 33. b7 Rb1 {Prevents Re6-b6} 34. Raa6 Nd7 35. e4 {[%eval -536,19]} (35. Rad6 $142 {[%eval -342,20]} Kf7 (35... R1xb7 $2 36. Re7 $19) 36. Re4 R1xb7 37. Rdd4) 35... R8xb7 {Black is clearly winning.} 36. e5 R7b2+ 37. Kf3 Rf1+ 38. Kg4 Re2 {Threatens to win with ...Rf1-f2!} 39. exf6 Nxf6+ {Weighted Error Value: White=0.47/Black=0.12 (very precise)} 0-1


