{D78: Fianchetto Grünfeld: 6 0-0 c6} 1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. d4 (4. O-O Nf6 5. b3 O-O 6. Bb2 c5 7. c4 Nc6 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Bxg7 Kxg7 10. d4 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4+ Nf6 13. Qe5 Qd6 14. Qxd6 exd6 15. Nc3 Rd8 16. Rfd1 a6 17. Rd4 Rb8 18. Rad1 Bf5 {1-0 Karjakin,S (2756)-Ponomariov,R (2731) Beijing Sportaccord blitz 2013 (11)}) 4... Nf6 5. O-O O-O 6. c4 $146 (6. b3 c5 7. Bb2 cxd4 (7... Ne4 8. Qc1 Nc6 9. dxc5 Nxc5 10. Bxg7 Kxg7 11. Rd1 e5 12. Qb2 f6 13. c4 d4 14. b4 Qb6 15. a3 a5 16. b5 Ne7 17. a4 Be6 18. Nbd2 Nc6 19. Ne1 Nb4 20. Ra3 Bf5 21. Nb3 Rac8 22. Rc1 {½-½ Grinza,A (2180)-Porchel,B (1978) Titled Tuesday intern op 06th Dec Late blitz 2022 (2) ½-½ Grinza,A (2180)-Porchel,B (1978) Titled Tuesday intern op 06th Dec Late Chess.com INT blitz 2022 (2)}) 8. Nxd4 Re8 9. c4 e5 10. Nf3 d4 11. e3 Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Bxf3 e4 14. Bg2 d3 15. Nd2 Nc6 16. Rc1 b6 17. Bxf6 Bxf6 18. Nxe4 Bg7 19. Nc3 Rc8 20. Bxc6 Rxc6 {1-0 Alinasab,M (2321)-Liyanage,R (2342) Titled Tuesday intern op 21st Feb Early blitz 2023 (4) 1-0 Alinasab,M (2321)-Liyanage,R (2342) Titled Tuesday intern op 21st Feb Early Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (4)} 21. Nd5 Qd7 22. Kg2 Qf5 23. Qd2 Bh6 24. Rcd1 Qe4+ 25. Kh2 Qf3 26. Qxd3 Bg7 27. Kg1 h5 28. h4 Be5 29. e4 Qg4 30. Kg2 Rce6 31. Qf3 Bb8 32. Nf6+ Rxf6 33. Qxf6 Qxe4+ 34. Qf3 Qe6 35. Rfe1 Qxe1 {1-0 Alingh Prins,J-Devriese,J NED-ch17 corr 1987 1-0 Alingh Prins,J-Devriese,J NED-ch17 corr Netherlands 1987}) 6... c6 7. Nbd2 a5 8. Ne5 ({RR} 8. Re1 Bf5 9. Qb3 Na6 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. a3 Qc7 12. Nb1 Bc2 13. Qb5 Qc8 14. Bf4 Nc7 15. Bxc7 Qxc7 16. Nc3 Qd6 17. Ne5 Rfd8 18. Rac1 Bf5 19. e3 Qa6 20. Qxa6 Rxa6 21. Na4 Nd7 22. Nxd7 Bxd7 {Illescas Cordoba,M (2617)-Salgado Lopez,I (2619) Linares 2014 ½-½ (52)}) 8... a4 $1 {[%mdl 4] now scores much better than the old 8...Ng4. punktet besser als das ältere 8...Sg4.} ({RR} 8... Ng4 9. Nxg4 Bxg4 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. h3 Bf5 12. g4 Bd7 13. Bxd5 Bc6 14. Bxc6 Nxc6 15. Nf3 Nxd4 16. Be3 Nxf3+ 17. exf3 b5 18. Qe2 Qd5 19. Rfd1 Qb7 20. Bd4 Rfd8 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 22. Rac1 Rxd1+ 23. Rxd1 {Jobava,B (2721)-Mamedyarov,S (2726) Tbilisi 2012 0-1 (52)}) ({RR} 8... Ng4 9. Ndf3 Nxe5 10. dxe5 dxc4 11. Qc2 Be6 12. Ng5 Qc8 13. f4 Na6 14. Bd2 Nb4 15. Qc1 b5 16. a3 Nd5 17. a4 Bg4 18. axb5 cxb5 19. Rf2 Qc5 20. h3 Bd7 21. Bxa5 b4 22. Bxd5 Qxd5 23. Bxb4 {Jelcic,M (2196)-Cansu,B (2014) Konjic 2023 ½-½ (52)}) 9. e3 Nbd7 10. f4 {[%eval -47,20]} (10. Nd3 $11 {[%eval 0,20] was preferrable.}) 10... c5 $146 ({Predecessor:} 10... Qa5 11. Kh1 e6 12. Qc2 Qa6 13. Rb1 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Ng4 15. Re1 f6 16. exf6 Nxf6 {½-½ Mamedyarov,S (2770)-Kamsky,G (2665) Titled Tuesday intern op 13th Apr blitz 2021 (5)}) ({RR} 10... Qa5 11. Kh1 e6 12. Qc2 Qa6 13. Rb1 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Ng4 15. Re1 f6 16. exf6 Nxf6 17. b3 e5 18. fxe5 Ng4 19. cxd5 cxd5 20. Bxd5+ Kh8 21. Nc4 Be6 22. Bg2 axb3 23. axb3 Rac8 24. Qe2 Rf2 25. Qd3 {Mamedyarov,S (2770)-Kamsky,G (2665) Chess.com INT 2021 ½-½}) 11. cxd5 cxd4 12. Ndc4 Nxe5 13. fxe5 Nxd5 14. Qxd4 Be6 {...Nd5-b4 would now be deadly.} 15. Nd2 {[%eval -160,19] [#]} (15. Bd2 $142 {[%eval -103,20]}) 15... Qb6 {[%eval -115,20]} 16. Nf3 Qxd4 17. exd4 h6 {Repels Nf3-g5} 18. Bd2 Rfc8 19. Rfc1 {Against Rc8-c2} Nb6 20. Ne1 Bd5 {[%eval -7,21]} (20... Rd8 $15 {[%eval -53,21] feels stronger.} 21. Be3 (21. Bxb7 Rab8 $17) 21... f6 22. exf6 Bxf6) 21. Bxd5 $11 Nxd5 22. Kf2 f6 23. Nd3 b6 (23... b5 {simplifies} 24. Rxc8+ Rxc8 25. Rc1 Rxc1 26. Bxc1 Kf7) 24. Kf3 Kf7 25. Ke4 e6 26. Nf4 fxe5 (26... b5 {looks sharper.} 27. g4 Nb6 28. exf6 Bxf6 29. Bb4 Rc4) 27. dxe5 Nxf4 28. Bxf4 b5 29. Be3 Ke8 30. b3 {[%eval 1,23]} (30. b4 $14 {[%eval 43,22]}) 30... Bf8 $1 {The position is equal.} 31. Rxc8+ Rxc8 32. Rf1 Bg7 {Inhibits Rf1-f6.} 33. Rd1 Bf8 {Wards off Rd1-d6} 34. Rf1 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.11 (very precise) /Black=0.09 (flawless)} 1/2-1/2


