{[%evp 0,79,19,31,25,-16,57,30,69,54,46,46,45,45,45,36,36,23,46,30,17,16,26,20,20,18,13,15,20,13,7,5,7,44,24,29,11,0,-29,-29,-29,-29,-29,12,12,-11,-14,-20,41,41,36,46,27,31,118,140,129,150,151,153,145,123,135,173,173,173,173,181,195,184,238,246,245,253,245,220,297,303,355,416,1020,990]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bf4 Ne4 7. Rc1 O-O (7... Nc6) 8. e3 ({RR} 8. h4 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Ba3 10. Rb1 c5 11. Qa4 Bf5 12. Rb3 c4 13. Rxa3 Nc6 14. Ne5 Qb6 15. f3 Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Qb2 17. Kf2 Rfe8 18. g4 Bc2 19. Qb4 Qc1 20. Bg2 Qd2 21. Qb2 {1-0 (21) Maghsoodloo,P (2706)-Serban,C (2332) Chess.com INT 2025}) 8... c5 9. Bd3 (9. dxc5 Nd7 10. Qxd5 $11 Ndxc5) 9... Nc6 (9... Nd7) ({RR} 9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nc6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. O-O Nxc3 13. bxc3 Bd6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. c4 Be6 16. cxd5 cxd5 17. Qa4 Rfd8 18. Rfd1 Rab8 19. Be2 Qb4 20. Qxa7 Ra8 21. Qd4 Qxd4 22. Rxd4 Rxa2 23. Bf3 f5 24. h4 {Fus,J (2425)-Costache,A (1973) Eforie Nord 2025 ½-½ (39)}) 10. O-O Nxc3 $146 {Hardly a home preparation, rather an attempt to avoid the well-forgotten theory.} ({RR} 10... Re8 11. dxc5 Nxc3 12. bxc3 Bxc5 13. Ng5 g6 14. Qf3 Qd7 15. Rfd1 Ne5 16. Qg3 Nxd3 17. Rxd3 Qf5 18. Rcd1 Be6 19. Qh4 h5 20. h3 Be7 21. Rd4 Qf6 22. g4 Qh8 23. Qg3 Bf6 24. e4 Bxd4 25. Rxd4 {Johansson,L (2463)-Kaasen,T (2462) Fagernes 2023 ½-½ (34)}) ({RR} 10... Re8 11. dxc5 Nxc3 12. bxc3 Bxc5 13. h3 h6 14. Bb1 Ne7 15. Qb3 Bd6 16. Bxd6 Qxd6 17. Rfd1 Qb6 18. Qa4 Bf5 19. Bxf5 Nxf5 20. Rb1 Qc6 21. Qb3 Ne7 22. Qxb7 Qxc3 23. Rdc1 Qa5 24. Rc7 Nf5 25. Rd1 {Mendonca,L (2562)-Visakh,N (2506) chess24.com INT 2022 1-0 (53)}) 11. bxc3 Ba3 12. Rb1 c4 {Logical: a counterblow in the centre in reply to a flank attack.} 13. Bc2 f5 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. Bxe5 Rf7 16. f3 (16. e4) 16... Be6 (16... a6) 17. e4 fxe4 $6 {Too aggressive. Black's king will be unsafe on the queenside.} ({There was nothing wrong with} 17... Qd7 $13 18. exf5 Bxf5 19. Bxf5 Rxf5 $1 {is now favorable for White.} 20. f4 $142) 18. fxe4 $2 {[%mdl 64] White misses a good opportunity:} Rxf1+ 19. Qxf1 Qd7 20. Qe2 Qc6 {Black has consolidated his position and got excellent counter-chances.} (20... Re8 21. h4 $18 {}) 21. Qh5 $6 (21. exd5 Bxd5 22. Bxg7 $18 {} Kxg7 23. Qe5+ Kg8 24. Qg5+ Kh8 25. Qf5 $16) 21... dxe4 {But this is not the best place for Black's king.} 22. Qg5 Bf8 23. Rf1 Bf7 $4 {[%mdl 8192] This blunder is a consequence of Black's inaccurate 21st move.} 24. h4 $1 {That's it. Black simply loses his crucial a4 pawn.} Qg6 25. Qf4 Bd5 26. h5 Qxh5 (26... Qe6 27. Bxe4 Bxe4 28. Qxe4) 27. Bxe4 {[%cal Ra2a4]} Bc6 {Desperation.} 28. Rf3 Qe8 (28... Bxe4 $40 29. Qxe4) 29. d5 $1 Bd7 30. d6 Be6 (30... Bc6 31. Bxc6 (31. Bxh7+ Kxh7 32. Qh4+ Kg8 33. Qxc4+ Kh7 34. Rh3+ Kg6 35. Qg4+ $15 Kf7 $5 36. Qf5+ Kg8 $17 {[%cal Ya6c7]} 37. Rh4 $5 {was safer} Rd8 $1 {, e.g.} 38. Qh7+ Kf7 39. Rf4+ Ke6 40. Qf5+ Kd5 41. Bf6+ Kxd6 42. Bxd8) 31... bxc6 32. Qxc4+ Kh8 33. Qd4 Qd7 34. c4) 31. Qh4 h6 32. Rg3 Bf5 33. Qf6 {Black can't successfully stop White's f6 pawn.} 1-0


