ite more chances in fighting for initative. For exemple,} h6 14. Bxf6 Nxf6 15. Ne5) 12... Bf8 $6 (12... Ndf6 $1 13. Bg5 (13. Ng5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Ng8 14. Nxe6 fxe6 15. Bf4 Nxf4 16. exf4 Bd6 (16... Nh6 17. Qd2 Nf5 $11) 17. Qd2 Qf6 18. Ne2 Ne7 $11) 13... h6 14. Bxf6 Nxf6 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '='} (14... Bxf6 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 15. O-O O-O $11) 15. O-O {The pawn placement on h3 allows Black to count on organizing an active counter-play on the K-side.} Rg8 $5 16. Qc2 g5 $132) 13. Bxf8 Kxf8 14. g4 (14. b4 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 14... Ng7 $6 (14... Nhf6 {was better.} 15. Ng5 Qe7 16. Qc2 h6 17. Nxe6+ Qxe6 18. O-O-O $14) 15. Qb3 (15. Qe2 Ne8 16. O-O-O Nd6 17. Ne5 $36 {looks even more energetically.}) (15. Qd2 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 15... Qb6 (15... h5 $5 16. gxh5 Rxh5 17. Qxb7 c5 $14 {Black is unlikely to have a sufficient compensation for a pawn, but he has a counter-play.}) (15... Qf6 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 16. Be2 Nb6 17. O-O-O $14) (15... Rb8 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 16. Qa3+ Kg8 17. O-O-O (17. Qxa7 $6 h5 18. Rg1 hxg4 19. hxg4 b5 $44) 17... h5 18. Qd6 $5 $14) 16. Qa3+ Kg8 17. O-O-O {White has a clear advantage.} a5 18. Qd6 Rc8 19. Ng5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Diagram [#]'} (19. Qg3 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Qc7 20. Ne5 $14) 19... Qc7 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!'} 20. Qxc7 (20. Qe7 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Ne5 $1 21. Qxc7 Nxd3+ 22. Kd2 Rxc7 23. Kxd3 h5 $11) 20... Rxc7 21. f4 Nf6 22. Rhg1 (22. Nxe6 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Nxe6 23. f5 Ng7 $1 24. Rhf1 g5 $1 25. e4 dxe4 26. Nxe4 Nxe4 27. Bxe4 Ne8 28. f6 h5 29. Rf5 hxg4 30. hxg4 Kf8 $11) 22... Bc8 23. Nf3 Re7 24. Ne5 Nfe8 (24... Nge8 $142 $11 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 25. e4 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!'} f6 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '?!' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Diagram [#]'} (25... Ne6 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 26. exd5 Nxf4 27. dxc6 bxc6 28. Nxc6 Rc7 29. d5 $14) 26. exd5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!'} fxe5 27. dxe5 (27. fxe5 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 27... Rf7 (27... cxd5 $142 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 28. Nxd5 $16) 28. f5 (28. d6 $142 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Rxf4 29. Bc2 Ne6 30. d7 Bxd7 31.