{C78: Ruy Lopez: Archangelsk and Möller Defences} 1. e4 {Marin,Mihail Kosten,Tony} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. a4 Rb8 8. c3 d6 9. d4 Bb6 $1 10. a5 (10. Na3 O-O 11. axb5 axb5 12. Nxb5 Bg4 13. Bc2 Bxf3 14. gxf3 Nh5 15. Be3 Qf6 16. Kh1 Ne7 17. Rg1 Ng6 18. Rg4 Nhf4 19. Bb3 c6 20. Na3 d5 21. exd5 cxd5 22. Nb5 Qc6 23. Ba4 f5 24. Rg3 e4 {½-½ Dominguez Perez,L (2655)-Miton,K (2638) La 98/253 Havana 2006}) 10... Ba7 ({RR} 10... Nxa5 11. Rxa5 Bxa5 12. dxe5 Ng4 13. Bg5 f6 14. exf6 gxf6 15. Bh4 c5 16. h3 h5 17. Nbd2 ({RR} 17. hxg4 hxg4 18. e5 gxf3 19. Bxf6 fxg2 20. Re1 Qd7 21. exd6+ Kf8) 17... Rb7 18. Bd5 Rg7 19. e5 Nxe5 20. Nxe5 dxe5 21. Ne4 Rh6 22. Qf3 Rgg6 23. Rd1 Kf8 24. Bf7) 11. h3 $1 {Against Bg4} O-O (11... Bb7 12. Be3 Nxe4 13. Re1 exd4 14. Bg5 Ne7 15. Nbd2 Nf6 16. Nh4 Qd7 17. Bxf6 gxf6 18. Qh5 Kd8 19. Qh6 dxc3 20. bxc3 d5 21. Ne4 Qc6 22. Nxf6 Qxc3 23. Qg7 {0-1 Antoniewski,R (2540)-Papp,G (2583) TCh-AUT 2016-17 (4.1)}) 12. Be3 {White is slightly better.} Ra8 $146 {12...Re8 is the modern continuation. 12...Te8 ist die moderne Fortsetzung. Kosten,Tony: 'The mainline, simply defending the a7-bishop.' Kosten,Tony: '12...Re8 is the modern continuation.' Kosten,Tony: '12...Te8 ist die moderne Fortsetzung.'} (12... Re8 13. Ng5 (13. Re1 {(Kosten,Tony) is Grischuk,A-Caruana,F.}) 13... Rf8 14. Re1 Ra8 15. Nf3 h6 16. Nbd2 exd4 17. cxd4 Nb4 18. e5 Nfd5 19. Ne4 Nxe3 20. Rxe3 Bb7 21. Rc1 dxe5 22. Nxe5 Bxd4 23. Qh5 Nd5 (23... Bxe5 24. Qxe5 Nd3 25. Rxd3 Qxd3 26. Nc5 Qd2 27. Rd1 Rae8 28. Rxd2 Rxe5 29. Nxb7 c5 30. f4 Re1+ 31. Kf2 Rc1 32. Bc2 c4 33. Nc5 b4 34. b3 Rc8 35. Nxa6 cxb3 36. Bxb3 R1c3 37. Rb2 {13. Ruy Lopez Archangelsk-Archangelsk 10...Ba7,1}) 24. Rf3 Qe7 (24... Bxe5 25. Qxe5 Qe7 26. Qd4 Qb4 27. Rd3 {13. Ruy Lopez Archangelsk-Archangelsk 10...Ba7,1}) 25. Nxf7 Qxe4 26. Rxc7 Nf4 27. Ng5+ {13. Ruy Lopez Archangelsk-Archangelsk 10...Ba7,1}) (12... exd4 $5 {(Kosten,Tony) has also been examined a few times,} 13. cxd4 Nb4 $1 (13... Nxe4 $2 {is a mistake, see Timofeev,A-Halkias,S.}) (13... h6 $6 {Zhigalko,S-Golubenko,V.}) 14. Nc3 {see Vachier Lagrave,M-Caruana,F.}) ({RR} 12... exd4) 13. Nbd2 Bb7 (13... h6 {(Kosten,Tony) see Kryvoruchko,Y-Durarbayli,V, also in the PGN Archive.}) ({RR} 13... h6 14. Re1 Re8 15. Qc2 exd4 16. Nxd4 Nxd4 17. cxd4 c5 18. e5 c4 19. exf6 cxb3 20. Qc6 Rb8 21. Bf4 Rxe1+ 22. Rxe1 Bb7 23. Qxd6 g5 24. Re7 gxf4 25. Qxf4 Qd5 26. Ne4 Qh5 27. Qg3+ Qg6 28. Qxg6+ {Saric,I (2689)-Maghsoodloo,P (2649) Batumi 2018 1-0 (63)}) 14. Re1 {Kosten,Tony: 'simply transposes.'} Re8 ({Black often prefers to stop a piece going to g5 with} 14... h6 {(Kosten,Tony) but if this isn't strictly necessary then the text is more accurate.} 15. Bc2 (15. Nf1 Re8 16. Ng3) 15... Re8 {Fedorchuk, S-Shirov,A, in the Archive.} {RR} 16. Qb1 exd4 17. cxd4 Nb4) (14... Nd7 $5 {(Kosten,Tony) is probably not very good, see Aagaard,J-Godena,M.}) ({RR} 14... Nd7 15. Bd5 Rb8 16. b4) ({RR} 14... h6 15. Bc2 Re8 16. d5 Ne7 17. Bxa7 Rxa7 18. b4 Ng6 19. c4 bxc4 20. Nxc4 Nf4 21. Ba4 Rf8 22. b5 axb5 23. Bxb5 Bc8 24. a6 Bd7 25. Na3 Nh7 26. Bf1 f5) ({RR} 14... exd4 15. cxd4 Nb4 16. Bg5 h6 17. Bh4 Nd3 18. Re3 Nf4 19. e5 dxe5 20. dxe5 Bxe3 21. fxe3 Ng6 22. exf6 Nxh4 23. Nxh4 Qxf6) 15. Ng5 {Kosten,Tony: 'Obviously critical, hitting f7.'} (15. Qc2 {(Kosten,Tony) supports e4,} h6 16. dxe5 Nxe5 17. Nxe5 dxe5 18. Bxa7 Rxa7 19. c4 Qe7 20. Rac1 Bc6 {so the rook can go to b7, Schwetlick,T (2488)-Rice,R (1367) ICCF email 2017, 1-0 (58).}) ({RR} 15. Nf1 exd4 16. cxd4 Rxe4) ({RR} 15. Bc2) ({RR} 15. Bc2 h6 16. dxe5 Bxe3 17. Rxe3 Nxe5 18. Qe2 c5 19. Nxe5 dxe5 20. c4 Nh5 21. Qxh5 Qxd2 22. Bb3 Qxb2 23. Rd1 Re7 24. Rd6 Qc1+ 25. Rd1 Qb2 26. Rg3 b4 27. Qxh6 f6 28. Qxf6 Rf7 29. Rd8+ Rxd8 {Aizenberg,B (2450)-Nurmanova,A (2315) Fujairah 2025 ½-½ (50)}) 15... Re7 {Kosten,Tony: '!'} (15... Rf8 {(Kosten,Tony) is sometimes played to offer a repetition, or simply to gain a bit of time on the clock.}) ({RR} 15... Rf8 16. Nf1 Ne7 ({RR} 16... h6 17. Nf3 Re8) 17. dxe5 Bxe3 ({RR} 17... dxe5 18. Qxd8) 18. Bxf7+) 16. Ndf3 $146 {Kosten,Tony: 'White is ready to capture on f7 and brings up some reinforcements.'} (16. d5 {Kosten,Tony} Nb8 {was annotated by Victor in Anand,V-Shirov,A.} (16... Bxe3 $5)) ({RR} 16. d5 Nb8 17. Bxa7 Rxa7 18. Nf1 c6 19. Ne3 ({RR} 19. dxc6 Nxc6) 19... cxd5 20. exd5 h6 21. Nf3 Rc7 22. Nd2 ({RR} 22. c4 Rc5) 22... Nbd7 23. c4 Nc5 ({RR} 23... Rc5 24. Ba2 bxc4 25. Ndxc4) 24. Bc2 ({RR} 24. cxb5 axb5) 24... b4 25. Ndf1 ({RR} 25. Nb3 Bc8 26. Nxc5 Rxc5 27. Qd2 Rb7) 25... Bc8 26. Ng3 g6 27. b3 Nh7 ({RR} 27... Rab7 28. Qd2 h5 29. Kh1 h4 30. Ngf1 Nh5) 28. Ne4 f5 ({RR} 28... Nxe4 29. Bxe4 Nf6 30. Nc2 ({RR} 30. Bd3 Nd7 31. Qd2 Nc5 32. Rab1 Qg5) 30... Rab7 31. Qd2 Nxe4 32. Rxe4 Bf5 33. Re2 Bxc2 34. Qxc2 Qg5) 29. Nxc5 Rxc5 30. Qd2 Rb7 {Anand,V (2790)-Shirov,A (2723) Wijk aan Zee 2010 CBM 135 [Marin,Mihail] 1-0 (55)}) ({RR} 16. Nf1 h6 17. d5 hxg5 18. dxc6 Bxc6 19. Bxg5 Nxe4 20. Bxe7 Qxe7 21. Ne3 Qf6 22. Qe2 g6 23. Rf1 Kg7 24. Nd5 Qh4 25. Nxc7 Rh8 26. Qf3 f5 27. Kh2 Nxf2 28. Ne6+ Kf6 29. Rxf2 Bxf2 30. Qd3 Be4 {Kosteniuk,A (2552)-Shirov,A (2630) Douglas 2017 0-1}) 16... h6 $1 {Kosten,Tony: 'This forces White's hand, but Black can hold his own in the resulting complications.'} 17. Nxf7 Rxf7 18. dxe5 Bxe3 $1 {Kosten,Tony: 'Forced.'} (18... dxe5 $2 {Kosten,Tony} 19. Qxd8+ Nxd8 20. Bxa7 Rxa7 21. Nxe5 {wins.}) 19. exf6 (19. Rxe3 $2 {Kosten,Tony} dxe5 {favours Black.}) 19... Ba7 {Kosten,Tony: 'A wild position, White will capture on f7 eventually and the material will be roughly equal but Black's king will be exposed.'} 20. fxg7 $146 {[%eval -39,25] [#] Kosten,Tony: 'N!?' Kosten,Tony: 'A new move, presumably home preparation.'} ({Predecessor:} 20. Bxf7+ $11 {[%eval 52,22] 20.e5 0.01} Kxf7 $11 {Kosten,Tony: 'transposes to the note below.'} 21. Qd5+ (21. e5 $5 {Kosten,Tony} dxe5 22. fxg7 Kxg7 23. Qe2) 21... Kf8 $1 (21... Kxf6 22. Qf5+ Ke7 23. e5 $16) 22. e5 (22. fxg7+ Kxg7 23. Rad1) 22... dxe5 23. fxg7+ Kxg7 24. Qe4 Qf6 {...Rg8 is the strong threat.} 25. Rad1 {Kosten,Tony: 'Kurmann,O (2466)-Kenneskog,T (2307) Sitges 2021, 1-0 (31), should be met by'} Rd8 $2 {[%eval 404,27] Wards off Rd7+} (25... Bc8 $1 $11 {[%eval 1,24] Kosten,Tony: '!'} 26. g4 {(Kosten,Tony) to stop ...Bf5,} b4) 26. Qg4+ $18 Kh7 $2 {[%eval 635,28]} (26... Qg6 {[%eval 367,25]}) 27. Rxd8 $18 Nxd8 28. Rxe5 Nf7 {[%eval 1224,24]} (28... Bxf3 $142 {[%eval 515,24]} 29. Qd7+ Kg6 30. Qd3+ Kg7) 29. Re6 {1-0 Kurmann,O (2466)-Kenneskog,T (2307) Sitges Sunway op 8th 2021 (4)}) (20. e5 $5 {(Kosten,Tony) is interesting:} dxe5 21. fxg7 Qe7 22. Re4 Kxg7 23. Rg4+ Kh8 24. Bxf7 Qxf7) 20... Qf6 $1 $15 {Kosten,Tony: '!' Kosten,Tony: 'Bringing the queen over to help her king.'} (20... Kxg7 {Kosten,Tony} 21. Bxf7 Kxf7 22. e5 dxe5 23. Qc2 Qf6 24. Qh7+ Qg7 25. Nxe5+ (25. Qf5+) 25... Nxe5 26. Qxg7+ Kxg7 27. Rxe5 {is the similar to the game, but the black king is on a worse square.}) 21. Qd5 {Chess con chili.} Kxg7 {[%eval 6,26] Kosten,Tony: 'Hastening the king out of the pin.'} (21... Qxg7 $1 $15 {[%eval -45,25]} 22. Qh5 {[%mdl 64] Pin} Raf8) 22. Qxf7+ {[%eval -51,26]} (22. e5 $1 $11 {[%eval 6,26] Kosten,Tony: 'is possible, and probably more precise:'} Nxe5 23. Qxb7 Nxf3+ 24. gxf3 Qxf3 (24... Qh4 {Kosten,Tony} 25. Qxa8 Qg3+ 26. Kh1 Qxh3+ {draws.}) 25. Qxf3 (25. Qxa6 $2 Bxf2+ {[%csl Oa6][%mdl 64] Discovered Attack, Double Attack} 26. Kh2 Qg3+ {[%mdl 64] Deflection} 27. Kh1 Qxh3#) 25... Rxf3 26. Bd5 Bxf2+ (26... Rxh3 $2 27. Bxa8 Rg3+ 28. Kf1 $18) 27. Kg2 Bxe1 28. Rxe1) 22... Qxf7 23. Bxf7 Kxf7 {Kosten,Tony: 'transposes.'} 24. e5 Nxe5 {[%eval 29,23] Kosten,Tony: '?!' Kosten,Tony: 'This is not forced.'} ({Black should try} 24... d5 $1 $15 {[%eval -53,23] Kosten,Tony: '!?'} 25. e6+ {Kosten,Tony} Ke7 26. Nh4 Kf6 {favours Black.}) 25. Nxe5+ $11 dxe5 26. Rxe5 Rg8 {[%eval 81,29] Kosten,Tony: 'transposes.'} (26... Rd8 $14 {[%eval 45,24] might be stronger.}) 27. g4 $16 {Kosten,Tony: 'An interesting endgame, White has rook and two pawns against two strong bishops.'} Rd8 {[%eval 117,24]} (27... Rg5 $14 {[%eval 53,27]} 28. Rae1 Bc5) 28. Rae1 $1 Rd7 {Prevents Re7+} 29. Kh2 {[%eval 21,22]} (29. b4 $16 {[%eval 112,23] Kosten,Tony: '!' Kosten,Tony: 'hinders Black's next possibility,'} Bd5 {Kosten,Tony} 30. Rf5+ Kg7 31. Re8 c6 32. Rfe5 {with some advantage, the a6-pawn might prove a problem.}) 29... c5 $2 {[%eval 223,25]} (29... Bd5 $11 {[%eval 21,22] and Black stays safe.}) (29... b4 $1 {Kosten,Tony} 30. Rf5+ (30. cxb4 Bd4 31. Rf5+ Kg7 32. Re6 Bd5 33. Rxa6 Be4 {wins an exchange.} 34. Kg1) 30... Kg7 31. Re6 b3 32. Kg3 Bd5 33. Rxa6 Bc5 {is unclear.}) 30. Rf5+ $18 Kg7 31. Kg3 {[%eval 122,24]} ({Only move:} 31. Re8 $1 $18 {[%eval 242,25]}) 31... Bb8+ $16 32. Kh4 $1 {Kosten,Tony: 'The white king is becoming active.'} Bc7 {[%eval 196,26]} (32... b4 $16 {[%eval 152,27] was worth a try.}) 33. Re6 $18 (33. Rxc5 Bd8+ 34. Kg3 Bxa5 $11) 33... Bd5 {[%eval 273,27]} (33... Bxa5 $142 {[%eval 163,28]} 34. Kh5 (34. Rxc5 Bd5 $11) 34... Bd8 35. Rg6+ {Kosten,Tony} Kh7 36. Rxh6+ Kg7 37. Rg6+ Kh7 38. f4 {the active rooks and advancing pawns will win.}) 34. Rxa6 (34. Rxd5 $2 Bd8+ 35. Kg3 Rxd5 36. Rxa6 Rd3+ 37. Kf4 Rd2 $17 (37... Rxh3 38. Ra8 $11)) 34... b4 {Kosten,Tony: '!'} 35. Kh5 Bf7+ {[#]} 36. Rxf7+ $1 {Deflection Kosten,Tony: 'The best chance.'} (36. Kh4 {Kosten,Tony} bxc3 37. bxc3 Bd8+ 38. Kg3 Bc4 39. Ra8 Bd3 40. Rxc5 Be7 41. Rcc8 Be4 {with plenty of counterplay.}) 36... Kxf7 (36... Rxf7 37. Rg6+ Kf8 38. a6 $11) 37. Kxh6 {[%eval 44,25]} (37. Ra7 $16 {[%eval 151,23]}) 37... bxc3 $14 38. bxc3 $18 {Endgame KRB-KR Kosten,Tony: 'White has 4 pawns for the piece, and good winning chances.'} Be5 $1 39. Rc6 Bxc3 {[%eval 121,22]} (39... Rd8 $1 $14 {[%eval 45,24] Kosten,Tony: '!' Kosten,Tony: 'is stronger,'} 40. Rxc5 {Kosten,Tony} Kf6 {threatening mate,} 41. Rc6+ Bd6 42. g5+ Kf5 43. g6 Rh8+ 44. Kg7 Be5+ 45. Kf7 Ra8 $1 {to play ...Ra7+, and amazingly this equal.}) 40. Rxc5 $16 Bd2+ 41. g5 Rd4 {Kosten,Tony: 'Threatening mate.'} 42. Kh5 {Prevents Rh4+.} Ra4 43. Rc7+ Kf8 44. Rd7 (44. h4 {(Kosten,Tony) is a good alternative,} Rxa5 45. Rc2 Bf4 46. Rc4 Bd6 47. f4 Kf7 48. Kg4 {and Black still has to play accurately to keep the pawns from advancing too far.}) 44... Bc3 (44... Be1 $1 {(Kosten,Tony) gains a tempo on the f-pawn.}) 45. Kg6 Rxa5 46. h4 $2 {[%eval 43,25] Kosten,Tony: 'The wrong pawn!'} (46. f4 $18 {[%eval 294,28]} Ra6+ {Kosten,Tony} 47. Kh7 Ra5 (47... Ra4 48. f5) 48. h4 Rf5 49. Rd8+ Ke7 50. Rd3 Bb2 51. Rf3 Ke6 52. Re3+ Kf7 53. h5 Rxf4 54. g6+ Kf8 55. h6 {and g7+.}) 46... Ra6+ $14 47. Kh7 {White has compensation.} Ra4 {Kosten,Tony: '!'} 48. h5 Rf4 $2 {[%eval 591,27]} (48... Ke8 $16 {[%eval 88,25] keeps some hope. Kosten,Tony: '!'} 49. Rc7 (49. Rd5 {Kosten,Tony} Ra7+ 50. Kh6 Kf7 {draws.}) 49... Bd2) 49. Rd3 $2 {[%eval 103,28] Kosten,Tony: 'White had to stop the rook check.'} (49. Rc7 $18 {[%eval 591,27] is the precise move to win.} Be5 {Kosten,Tony} 50. Rc8+ Ke7 51. Rc5 Bb2 52. Rc2 Rb4 53. h6 Rb7 54. f4 Ke8+ 55. Kg6 {the pawns can't be stopped.}) 49... Rf7+ $16 50. Kg6 Rg7+ 51. Kh6 $1 Rc7 52. f4 $1 Rc6+ $2 {[%eval 262,30]} (52... Kf7 $16 {[%eval 111,27] Kosten,Tony: '!'}) 53. Kh7 {[%eval 106,25]} Rc7+ 54. Kg6 Rc6+ {[#]} {Weaker is} 55. Kh7 {[%eval -1,24]} (55. Kf5 $1 $16 {[%eval 111,30]}) 55... Rc7+ $1 $16 56. Kh6 Rc6+ $1 {[#]} 57. g6 $1 $18 {[%eval 262,30] is more deadly. Kosten,Tony: '!'} Bf6 58. Ra3 Rc8 {Against Ra8} 59. Ra6 Bc3 60. Ra7 $2 {[%eval 1,28]} (60. Kg5 $18 {[%eval 229,28] Kosten,Tony: '!' Kosten,Tony: 'to play h5-h6.'} Rc5+ $2 {Kosten,Tony} 61. f5 Bd2+ 62. Kg4) 60... Kg8 $1 61. Kg5 Rc5+ $1 62. Kg4 (62. f5 {Kosten,Tony} Bd2+ 63. Kf6 Bc3+ {draws.}) 62... Rc6 $1 63. Rd7 {Kg5 would now be deadly.} Bb2 $1 64. Rd8+ Kg7 65. Rd7+ Kg8 66. Kg5 Rc5+ $1 {The position is equal.} 67. Kh6 Bf6 {Against Rd8+ Kosten,Tony: 'Stopping Rd8 mate. Now Black is drawing.'} 68. Rf7 Rc6 (68... Rf5 {Kosten,Tony}) 69. Ra7 {Intending Ra8+ and mate.} Rd6 70. Ra8+ Rd8 $1 71. Ra7 Rd6 72. Rb7 Rd8 73. f5 Rd6 74. Ra7 Rd8 75. Ra6 Rf8 76. Rc6 Bd8 77. Re6 Bf6 {Kosten,