1. e4 {Roiz,M} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. h3 e5 {'!' '!' The main line 6...e5 scores better than 6...e6. Die Hauptvariante 6...e5 punktet besser als 6...e6. The main line 6...e5 scores better than 6...e6. Die Hauptvariante 6...e5 punktet besser als 6...e6.} 7. Nf3 {Roiz,M: 'This retreat became quite popular these last 2 years.'} Qc7 {Roiz,M: 'One of a few reasonable ways to meet White's setup. As usual, this move is mainly aimed at preventing Bc4.'} (7... Be7 {- 152/84}) 8. Nh2 (8. g4 {Roiz,M} h6 {leads to double-edged play, as in Ponkratov,P (2623) -Bocharov,D (2528) Khanty-Mansiysk RUS 2020 [Roiz,M]}) 8... Nbd7 $146 {Roiz,M: 'Parham comes up with a natural novelty. Black connects his knights to maintain control of d5.'} ({Predecessor:} 8... Be6 9. Be2 (9. Ng4 {Roiz,M} Nbd7 10. Ne3 Qc6 $11) 9... Nbd7 10. a4 Be7 11. Ng4 Qc6 12. Bf3 O-O {Roiz,M: '=' Roiz,M: 'lead to an approximate equality in Nestorovic,N - Lazov,T Paracin 2017'} 13. O-O b5 14. Ne3 b4 {1-0 Nestorovic,N (2509)-Lazov,T (2279) Paracin Summer op-A 10th 2017 (7.17) 1-0 Nestorovic,N (2509)-Lazov,T (2279) Paracin Summer op-A 10th 2017 (7.17)}) 9. Ng4 ({RR} 9. Be3 b5 10. g4 b4 11. Nd5 Nxd5 12. exd5 Be7 13. g5 Nb6 14. Qf3 Nc4 15. O-O-O Nxe3 16. Qxe3 Bf5 17. Bd3 Bxd3 18. Rxd3 Rc8 19. Rd2 Qc5 20. Qg3 h6 21. gxh6 Rxh6 22. Kb1 Rg6 23. Qd3 Qc4 {Perossa,N (2244)-Akhvlediani,I (2360) Arco 2024 0-1 (51)}) 9... b5 {'Black had no reason for delaying the standard counter-attacking advance.'} ({Less precise is} 9... Be7 {Roiz,M} 10. a4 O-O 11. Bd3 Nc5 12. Nxf6+ Bxf6 13. Nd5 $14) 10. Ne3 Nb6 $1 ({Roiz,M: 'Less precise is'} 10... Bb7 11. a4 {Roiz,M: '!'} b4 12. Ncd5 {Roiz,M: ''} Bxd5 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. Qxd5 Nb6 15. Qa5 $16) 11. a3 $146 ({Roiz,M: 'After'} 11. a4 b4 12. Na2 (12. a5 bxc3 13. axb6 Qxb6 (13... cxb2 14. Bb5+ $1 axb5 15. Rxa8 bxc1=Q 16. Qxc1 Qc6 17. Qa1 Be7 18. Qa7 O-O 19. Rxc8 Qxc8 20. Qxe7 Qb8 21. Qa7 Qxa7 22. bxa7 Ra8 23. f3 Rxa7 24. Ke2 Kf8 25. Rb1 Ra5 $13) 14. bxc3 Qc6 15. Bc4 Be6 16. Bd5 Bxd5 17. exd5 Qxc3+ 18. Bd2 Qc7 19. c4 Be7 20. Qa4+ Qd7 21. Qc6 O-O $13) (12. Ncd5 Nbxd5 13. exd5 (13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. Qxd5 Bb7 15. Qd3 Be7 16. Be3 O-O $15) 13... Be7 14. Bd3 O-O 15. Bd2 Rb8 $13) 12... a5 13. c3 (13. Bb5+ {Roiz,M} Bd7 $132 {White doesn't seem to achieve much because of the poor Na2.}) 13... d5 $1 14. Nxd5 Nbxd5 15. exd5 Bc5 16. Bb5+ Bd7 17. Bxd7+ Qxd7 18. O-O O-O 19. c4 Ne4 20. Qd3 f5 $44) ({RR} 11. Bd3 Be7 12. O-O O-O 13. a3 g6 14. Qf3 Bb7 15. Rd1 Rad8 16. Ng4 Nxg4 17. hxg4 f5 18. gxf5 Rxf5 19. Qg3 Rf7 20. Bh6 Bf8 21. Bg5 Be7 22. Bh6 Kh8 23. Be2 g5 24. Bh5 Rf4 25. Bxg5 Bxg5 {Zhapova,Y (2110)-Bodnaruk,A (2340) Sochi 2023 ½-½ (46)}) 11... Be7 12. Bd3 Be6 {Roiz,M: 'Both sides have almost mobilized their forces.'} 13. Qf3 g6 {Roiz,M: 'Parham reasonably decides to prevent Nf5. Black can cope with weakening his k-side a bit.'} ({Possible was also} 13... O-O {Roiz,M} 14. Nf5 d5 15. exd5 Nfxd5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. O-O Rad8 $11) 14. O-O Nfd7 $6 {Roiz,M: 'Quite a risky approach. Black leaves his king in the centre for a while to exchange the Bd3.'} ({Roiz,M: 'Somewhat more natural looks'} 14... O-O 15. Bd2 Qb7 16. Rfd1 Nfd7 (16... Rfc8 $11 {Roiz,M}) 17. Be2 Rab8 18. Be1 f5 $1 19. exf5 gxf5 20. Qxb7 Rxb7 21. g3 Rc7 $13) 15. Bd2 Nc5 16. Be2 ({Another decent way of handling the position was} 16. b4 $5 {Roiz,M} Nxd3 17. cxd3 O-O 18. Nf5 $14 {The knight is untouchable, so Black's king comes under pressure.}) 16... O-O {Diagram [#]} 17. Nf5 $6 {Roiz,M: 'White chooses a wrong moment for attacking measures.'} ({Roiz,M: 'More promising was'} 17. b4 {Roiz,M: '!'} Nca4 (17... Ncd7 18. a4 bxa4 19. Nxa4 Nc4 20. Nxc4 Bxc4 21. Nc3 Nb6 22. Rfb1 Bxe2 23. Qxe2 Qc4 24. Qe1 $16) 18. Nxa4 Nxa4 (18... bxa4 19. c4 $16) 19. c4 $1 bxc4 20. Rfc1 c3 21. Nd1 Rfc8 (21... c2 {Roiz,M} 22. Ne3 $14 {, regaining the pawn in a favorable situation.}) 22. Nxc3 Nxc3 23. Rxc3 Qb7 24. Rac1 $14) 17... Bxf5 ({Roiz,M: 'it was also possible to accept the challenge:'} 17... gxf5 18. exf5 Kh8 19. b4 Ncd7 {Roiz,M: '⇆' Roiz,M: 'Black's chances are by no means worse.'} 20. fxe6 fxe6 21. Qg4 Rae8 (21... Rf6 22. Bd3 Rg8 23. Qh5 Nf8 $15) 22. Rad1 Bd8 $15) 18. exf5 d5 $15 {Roiz,M: '!' Roiz,M: 'The strong pawn centre fully compensates White's bishop pair.'} 19. Bh6 Rfd8 20. Rad1 ({Also after} 20. Qg3 {Roiz,M} Bf6 21. fxg6 hxg6 22. f4 e4 {White fails to create serious threats against Kg8.}) 20... e4 21. Qg4 Nca4 {Roiz,M: 'GM Maghsoodloo is putting strong pressure on White's q-side.'} ({Worthy of attention is also} 21... Qe5 $5 {Roiz,M} 22. fxg6 hxg6 23. Bf4 Qe6 {with excellent play.}) 22. Nxa4 Nxa4 23. fxg6 hxg6 {Diagram [#]} 24. f4 $2 {Roiz,M: 'This impulsive move is the main cause of Pragg's defeat in this game.'} ({Roiz,M: 'It was necessary to defend calmly with'} 24. Rb1 Qc8 (24... Qxc2 $2 25. Rfc1 Qb3 26. h4 $16) 25. Qf4 Qe6 26. c3 {Roiz,M: 'Possibly Black is a bit better here, but all the struggle is ahead.'} Rac8 $15) 24... Qb6+ 25. Kh1 f5 {Roiz,M: '!' Roiz,M: 'A very convincing way of securing the Kg8. White is positionally busted from now on.'} 26. Qg3 Nxb2 27. Rb1 Nc4 {Roiz,M: '-+' Roiz,M: 'Black is up a pawn in a better position.'} (27... Na4 28. c4 Rac8 29. cxb5 Nc3 30. Rb2 Nxe2 31. Rxe2 d4 $19) 28. a4 Kh7 {Roiz,M: '?!'} (28... Rd6 $19) ({The simple} 28... b4 {Roiz,M} 29. Bg5 Bxg5 30. Qxg5 Rd6 $19 {would have kept everything under control.}) 29. Bxc4 {Roiz,M: '?' Roiz,M: 'Immediately returning the favor!'} ({Roiz,M: 'It was necessary to play'} 29. Bg5 {Roiz,M: '!'} Bxg5 30. fxg5 Rac8 31. Qh4+ (31. Bxc4 {Roiz,M} Rxc4 32. Qh4+ Kg8 33. axb5 axb5 34. Qh6 $17 {The limited material balance leaves White some drawing chances.}) 31... Kg8 32. axb5 axb5 33. Qh6 Qd6 34. Rxb5 Ne5 35. Rb7 Rd7 $19) 29... Kxh6 30. Bb3 Rac8 31. axb5 axb5 {Roiz,M: 'It is only a matter of time before Black's connected pawns will decide the game.'} 32. Rfd1 d4 33. Qf2 Rc3 {Roiz,M: 'Full domination!'} 34. Ra1 Qf6 (34... e3 35. Qe1 (35. Qf3 d3 $19) 35... Rxb3 36. cxb3 d3 $19) 35. Ra7 Qh4 {Roiz,M: 'Of