{D51: Queen's Gambit Declined: 4 Bg5 Nbd7 sidelines} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Bb4 7. e3 c6 $146 {7...g5 is the modern continuation. 7...g5 ist die moderne Fortsetzung.} (7... c5 8. Qc2 Qa5 9. Nd2 cxd4 10. exd4 O-O 11. Be2 dxc4 12. Nxc4 Qd5 13. O-O-O Bxc3 14. bxc3 Nb6 15. Nd2 Qd8 16. Ne4 Nbd5 17. c4 Qc7 18. Bg3 Qa5 19. cxd5 Nxe4 20. Qxe4 exd5 21. Qc2 Bf5 22. Qxf5 {½-½ Rabinovich,I-Sergeev,A URS-ch04 Leningrad 1925 (16)}) ({RR} 7... c5 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Be2 Qa5 10. O-O O-O 11. dxc5 Bxc3 12. bxc3 Qxc5 13. Qd4 g5 14. Bg3 Ne4 15. Rac1 Re8 16. Rfd1 Nb6 17. a4 Qxd4 18. Rxd4 Nc5 19. Bb5 Nb3 20. Bxe8 Nxc1 21. Bb5 Bd7 22. Kf1 {Rychagov,A (2543)-Sarana,A (2717) Chess.com INT 2024 0-1}) ({RR} 7... g5 8. h3 gxh4 9. cxd5 exd5 10. Bd3 Ne4 11. O-O Bxc3 12. bxc3 Nb6 13. Rc1 Rg8 14. Kh1 Nd6 15. Ne5 Qg5 16. Rg1 Bf5 17. f4 Qf6 18. Be2 Ne4 19. Qe1 Ng3+ 20. Kh2 Nxe2 21. Qxe2 Be4 22. Qh5 {Matyunin,M (2099)-Corrales Jimenez,F (2540) Chess.com INT 2025 0-1 (55)}) 8. Nd2 $146 ({RR} 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O b6 10. Bg3 Bb7 11. Rc1 Rc8 12. a3 Bxc3 13. Rxc3 c5 14. Bd6 Re8 15. b4 cxd4 16. exd4 dxc4 17. Rxc4 Rxc4 18. Bxc4 Nb8 {½-½ (18) Fejzullahu,J-Milinovikj,A Skopje 2024}) ({RR} 8. a3 Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Qa5 10. Qb3 c5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Qb5+ Qxb5 13. cxb5 Ne4 14. Bd3 b6 15. Bxe4 dxe4 16. Nd2 cxd4 17. exd4 Bb7 18. O-O O-O 19. Rac1 Rfd8 20. a4 e5 21. Nb3 Rd5 22. Rfd1 exd4 {Carlsen,J (1431)-Hansen,S (1420) Ringsted 2002 ½-½}) 8... a5 $5 {Exploring less charted territory. Erkundet wenig bekanntes Terrain.} 9. Be2 $146 {White is slightly better.} ({Predecessor:} 9. Qc2 O-O 10. Bd3 Re8 11. a3 Be7 12. O-O e5 13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. Bxe7 Nxe7 15. Nf3 exd4 16. exd4 {[%eval -1,18] 0-1 (47) Teodorescu,R-Stanciu,T Eforie Nord 2001} (16. Nxd4 $14 {[%eval 54,19]} Nf6 17. h3)) 9... O-O 10. O-O b6 11. Rc1 Bb7 12. cxd5 exd5 13. Bd3 Re8 14. Re1 Qb8 15. Bf5 Bd6 16. Nf3 g6 17. Bxd7 Nxd7 18. e4 dxe4 19. Nxe4 Bb4 $2 {[%eval 230,20] [#]} (19... c5 $14 {[%eval 33,18]} 20. dxc5 Bxc5) 20. Re3 {[%eval 82,19]} (20. Ne5 $1 $18 {[%eval 230,20][%cal Re5d7] is more deadly.} Nxe5 21. Nf6+ (21. dxe5 Bxe1 22. Nf6+ Kh8 $14) 21... Kh8 22. Re3 {[%mdl 64] Pin} (22. Rxe5 Rxe5 23. dxe5 Qxe5 $11) (22. dxe5 Bxe1 23. Nxe8 Bxf2+ 24. Bxf2 Qxe8 $11)) 20... Qf4 $16 21. Bg3 (21. Ne5 {keeps more tension.} Nxe5 22. Nf6+ Kh8 23. g3) 21... Qf5 22. Ne5 Nxe5 23. dxe5 Be7 {Inhibits Ne4-f6+.} 24. Nd6 Bxd6 25. Qxd6 Rac8 {[%eval 102,18] Black is weak on the dark squares} (25... c5 $14 {[%eval 66,16] is superior.}) 26. Rd1 {[%eval 63,19]} (26. h3 $16 {[%eval 102,18]}) 26... Qe6 27. Rb3 b5 28. h4 a4 29. Qxe6 {[%eval 47,19]} (29. Rb4 $16 {[%eval 83,20]}) 29... Rxe6 $14 30. Rb4 Ba6 31. Rbd4 c5 32. Rd8+ Kg7 33. Rxc8 Bxc8 $11 {Endgame. KRB-KRB} 34. Bf4 b4 35. Rc1 Rc6 36. a3 bxa3 37. bxa3 c4 38. Bd2 Be6 39. Bb4 g5 40. hxg5 hxg5 41. f3 g4 42. Kf2 Kg6 43. fxg4 Bxg4 44. Ke3 Rc8 45. Kd4 Be6 46. Rc3 Kf5 47. Rf3+ Kg4 48. Rc3 Rd8+ 49. Kc5 Kf4 50. Kb5 Kxe5 51. Kxa4 Kd4 52. Rc1 Rb8 53. Rd1+ Ke3 54. Rc1 Bd5 {[%eval -18,17]} ({Black should try} 54... Rc8 $17 {[%eval -72,20]}) 55. Rc2 {[%eval -68,21]} (55. Re1+ $11 {[%eval -18,17]} Kf2 56. Re5 Bc6+ 57. Ka5) 55... f5 $15 56. g3 Rc8 57. Kb5 {[%eval -109,24]} ({White should play} 57. Rd2 $1 $15 {[%eval -58,21]} Be4 58. Bc3) 57... Be4 $17 58. Rc1 (58. Rxc4 $2 {is the wrong capture.} Bd3 59. Bc5+ Kf3 $19) 58... Bd3 {aiming for ...c4-c3+.} 59. Kb6 Rg8 60. Be1 Ra8 61. Bb4 Rg8 {[%eval 1,17]} (61... Ke4 $15 {[%eval -58,18]}) 62. Be1 $1 $11 Ke2 {And now ...f5-f4! would win.} 63. a4 {[#]} f4 $1 64. gxf4 Rg1 65. a5 $2 {[%eval -837,23]} Rxe1 $19 66. Rxe1+ Kxe1 {Black mates.} 67. a6 c3 68. a7 Be4 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.11 (very precise) /Black=0.12 (very precise)} 0-1


