{[%evp 0,26,22,22,18,12,12,12,12,-13,-13,1,-2,0,16,11,19,34,45,33,57,53,61,53,55,57,78,53,74]} {Magsodloo promised to become really top Worls player few years ago ,but it seems that he slowed down. But in this game World Champion was in troubles!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be2 a6 7. O-O Nf6 8. Be3 d6 9. f4 Be7 $5 {Telling honestly, this Carlsbad system is not easy to handle with Black.So,Magnus wants to create some nonclassical set ups.} 10. a4 O-O 11. Kh1 Bd7 12. Nb3 b6 13. Bf3 $5 $146 {New and interesting. .} Rab8 14. g4 {Novelty of Iranian Grandmaster.It was tried a bit different Knight transfer} Bc8 15. g5 Nd7 $2 {Overoptimistic.Preferable was to transfer Knight to e6.} 16. Bg2 Re8 17. Qh5 g6 18. Qh3 (18. Qh4) 18... Bf8 $6 (18... Nb4 19. Nd4) 19. f5 Nde5 {[#]} 20. Rf4 $1 Nb4 (20... Na5 21. Raf1 Nac4 {Better would be} 22. Bc1 {after what White can hold the initiative ,sacrificing a piece} b5 23. axb5 axb5 24. Rh4 h5 25. gxh6 Kh7 $1 26. Rhf4 (26. Nd4) 26... Qe7 {Magbus did not want to give up the center} 27. fxg6+ fxg6 28. Nd4) 21. Nd4 Nc4 $146 ({RR} 21... exf5 22. exf5 Bg7 23. Rh4 gxf5 24. Rxh7 Qc4 25. Bg1 Ng6 26. Rxg7+ Kxg7 27. b3 Qc7 28. Nxf5+ Bxf5 29. Bd4+ Re5 30. Qxf5 Qe7 31. Rf1 Qe6 32. Bxe5+ Nxe5 33. Qf4 a5 34. Ne2 Nxc2 35. Be4 Nb4 36. Nd4 {Kitsune-Auryn Playchess.com INT 2007 1-0 (39)}) 22. Bg1 (22. Rh4 h5 ({White could keep extra pawn with} 22... h6 {but Blacks Bishop pair would be some compensation for it.} {There were two other promising optios here} 23. Rxh6 {and} Bxh6 {Strong pressure keeps White after} 24. Qxh6) 23. gxh6 Kh7 24. fxg6+ fxg6 25. Nf3) 22... exf5 (22... e5 23. Rh4 h5 24. Nde2 $1) 23. exf5 Bb7 24. Raf1 (24. Rh4 Bxg2+ 25. Kxg2 {Magnus would keep compensation even after better} h5 (25... Qb7+ 26. Nf3) 26. gxh6) 24... Bxg2+ 25. Qxg2 $2 Qb7 26. Nf3 (26. Qxb7 Rxb7 27. Nc6 {Similar development would follow after} Nxc6 28. Nd5 Be7 29. f6) 26... b5 27. axb5 axb5 28. Bd4 Nd5 {Now starts forced variation ,where Magnus 