exc4 $1 bxc4 18. e5 Bxe5 ({Mikhalchishin,Adrian: 'White would have strong initiative after'} 18... Nbd5 19. exd6 Qxd6 20. Nxc4 Qd8 21. Ba5 Qd7 22. Rc1 (22. Ne5) 22... Kg8 23. Re1 $40) 19. dxe5 Nd3 20. Ba5 $1 Qc5 (20... Qxa5 21. Nxc4 Qb4 22. Qxd3 g6 23. Nd6 Kg7 24. Rfc1 Rf8 25. Rc7 $16) 21. Nxc4 $1 (21. b4 $5 Qd4 (21... cxb3 22. Qxd3 Qxa5 23. Nc4 Qc7 24. Nd6 Bd7 25. Rab1 Qb6 26. Rfd1 Bc6 27. Nc4 Qc7 28. Rxb3 $16) 22. Bc7 Rb7 23. Nc2 Qd7 24. Bd6 Kg8 25. Ne3 $16) 21... Qxc4 22. Ra3 {Mikhalchishin,Adrian: '!'} Nd5 (22... Bb7 23. Bxb7 Rxb7 24. Rxd3 g6 25. Bd8 Qb5 26. Rb3 Qxb3 27. Bxe7+ Kxe7 28. Qd6+ Ke8 29. Rc1 $18) 23. Rxd3 h6 ({Immediately losing was} 23... Rxb2 24. Rc3 $1) 24. Rc3 {Mikhalchishin,Adrian: '!'} Qb5 {Diagram [#]} 25. Bc7 $1 Ra8 26. Rc5 $18 Qb7 ({Nice variation was after capture} 26... Qxb2 27. Bd6+ Kg8 28. Rxd5 exd5 29. Qxd5 Ra7 30. Qc5) 27. Bd6+ Kg8 28. Rxd5 $1 {Idea is practically the same.} exd5 29. Bxd5 Qa7 30. Qf3 {1-0 (30) Can,E (2592)-Maghsoodloo,P (2721) Mayrhofen 2022 CBM 212 Extra [Mikhalchishin,Adrian]} 1-0


