{E10: Blumenfeld Gambit} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 h6 $146 (3... c5 4. Nc3 (4. g3 cxd4 5. Nxd4 a6 6. Bg2 Qc7 7. Qd3 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc3 Rd8 10. b3 d6 11. Bb2 Bd7 12. Rac1 Be8 13. Rfd1 Nbd7 14. h3 Rac8 15. g4 Ne5 16. Qe3 Qb8 17. f4 Nc6 18. Nxc6 Bxc6 {0-1 Ollitervo,T (2425)-Visakh,N (2405) Deutsche Schz-5 corr3435 1934}) 4... cxd4 5. Nxd4 a6 6. g3 Qc7 7. Bg2 Nc6 (7... Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Bf4 d6 10. Nb3 Nbd7 11. Rc1 Nh5 12. Be3 Ne5 13. Na4 Bd7 14. Nb6 Rad8 15. Qd2 Be8 16. Qa5 Kh8 17. f4 Ng4 18. Bd2 Ngf6 19. e4 Bc6 20. Rfe1 Ne8 21. Nd5 Qxa5 22. Bxa5 {1-0 Dautov,R (2615)-Lutz,C (2555) 66/458 Nussloch 1996}) 8. O-O Be7 9. b3 O-O 10. Bb2 d6 11. Rc1 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Bd7 13. Rfd1 Rfd8 14. h3 Rac8 15. e3 Qb8 16. a4 Bc6 17. e4 b5 18. cxb5 {1-0 Gheng,J (2576)-Brittner,S (2046) Enghien les Bains 2003 (1)}) 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Be7 6. Bg2 O-O ({RR} 6... d5 7. O-O O-O 8. Qc2 c6 9. Rd1 Nbd7 10. Bf4 a5 11. a3 a4 12. Nc3 Qa5 13. Ne5 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Nd7 15. cxd5 exd5 16. Rac1 Nb6 17. e4 Bg4 18. Rd3 Rfd8 19. h3 Be6 20. exd5 cxd5 21. Qd1 {Le,Q (2729)-Gukesh,D (2776) Saint Louis 2025 0-1 (42)}) 7. Qc2 d5 8. h4 {[%eval -14,22]} (8. O-O $14 {[%eval 38,22]}) 8... Nbd7 $146 ({RR} 8... c6 9. Nc3 Nbd7 10. e4 Nxe4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Qxe4 c5 13. Bc3 Nf6 14. Qc2 cxd4 15. O-O-O e5 16. Nxe5 Qc7 17. Bxd4 Be6 18. Kb1 Rad8 19. f4 Qc8 20. Ka1 Rd6 21. Bf3 b5 22. c5 Rfd8 23. Bf2 {Mitsis,G (2376)-Zoler,D (2485) Eforie Nord 2025 0-1 (99)}) 9. Nc3 dxc4 10. Rd1 c5 11. dxc5 Qc7 12. c6 {[%eval -70,22]} bxc6 $15 (12... Qxc6 13. g4 $11) 13. O-O Nd5 14. Nd4 {[%eval -93,21] White is on the road to losing.} (14. Qa4 $15 {[%eval -53,22]}) 14... Rb8 15. Bxd5 {[%eval -187,27]} (15. b3 $17 {[%eval -71,22] was called for.}) 15... exd5 $19 (15... cxd5 16. Bf4 Qb6 17. Bxb8 Nxb8 18. e4 $11) 16. e4 Bc5 17. Bf4 Ne5 18. Kg2 {[%eval -306,21] Wards off Bh3+} (18. Qe2 $142 {[%eval -180,26]} f6 19. exd5 cxd5 20. Nxd5) 18... f6 19. f3 Bd6 20. exd5 {Black must now prevent Nxc6.} Nd3 {[#] Discovered Attack} 21. Bc1 {[%eval -401,22]} (21. Bxd6 {[%eval -276,23] was forced.} Qxd6 22. b3) 21... cxd5 (21... Bxg3 22. dxc6 Be5 (22... Bxh4 23. Nce2 $17) 23. Nd5 $17) 22. Ndb5 $2 {[%eval -640,24]} (22. b3 {[%eval -387,22]} Qd7 (22... Bxg3 23. Nxd5 Qd6 24. Qxc4 $15) 23. Rh1) 22... Qd7 {(  ...Qh3+). Black is clearly winning.} 23. Nxd6 Qh3+ {Deflection} 24. Kg1 {[#] And now Nxc8 would win.} Qxg3+ 25. Qg2 Qxd6 26. Bxh6 Rf7 ({Worse is} 26... Nxb2 27. Qxg7#) 27. Rd2 Bf5 28. Ne2 Re8 {White is weak on the light squares} 29. Ng3 Qd7 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.78/Black=0.04 (flawless)} 0-1


