1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Nbd7 8. Qe2 Qc7 9. O-O-O b5 10. a3 Rb8 11. g4 (11. Nd5 {- 16/472 Bronstein,David 2585 - Gheorghiu,Florin 2530, Petropolis (izt) 1973 - 16/472}) 11... h6 12. Bh4 Be7 13. Bg2 b4 {Black is seeking chances on the queenside, thus reaching a highly double-edged position. Precise play is much required on both sides.} 14. axb4 Rxb4 15. Be1 Qb6 16. Bf2 {Diagram [#]} Rxb2 $146 ({Much better is} 16... Qc7 17. h4 (17. Bf3 Nb6 18. Na2 Ra4 19. Kb1 d5 $13) 17... h5 18. g5 Ng4 $13 {with unclear play, as in Magshoodloo's games against Cheparinov some 10 days later.}) {Diagram [#] Diagram [#]} 17. Ndb5 $1 Qa5 (17... Nc5 18. Kxb2 O-O (18... Nfd7 19. Bxc5 Nxc5 20. Kc1 axb5 21. Qxb5+ Nd7 22. Qxb6 Nxb6 23. h4 $18) 19. Bxc5 dxc5 20. e5 Nd7 21. Rhe1 $16) 18. Kxb2 Qb4+ 19. Kc1 axb5 {Diagram [#]} 20. Kd2 $1 {This king walk brings White some advantage.} (20. Nb1 $2 Nc5 21. c3 Qa5 $17) 20... O-O ({Black can put stronger resistance after} 20... g5 21. Rb1 Qc4 22. Rxb5 Qxe2+ 23. Nxe2 gxf4 (23... Nxg4 24. Bd4 e5 25. fxe5 dxe5 26. Bc3 $16) 24. h3 (24. Nxf4 Nxg4 25. Bg3 Bg5 26. h4 Bf6 27. Nd3 $14) 24... Ba6 25. Rb3 Bxe2 26. Kxe2 O-O 27. Rhb1 $14 {with somewhat better position for White.}) 21. Rb1 Qa5 22. Rxb5 ({Probably stronger is} 22. Qxb5 $142 Qc7 23. h3 g5 24. Ra1 gxf4 25. Ra7 Qd8 26. Rb1 $14) {Diagram [#]} 22... Qc7 $2 {The crucial mistake. Black misses the opportunity to generate some counter-chances.} ({After} 22... Qa8 {win10: '!'} 23. g5 (23. h4 Ba6 24. g5 Bxb5 25. Qxb5 Rb8 26. Qe2 Nh7 27. gxh6 Qa5 $15) (23. Rg1 {win10: '!'} Ba6 24. e5 d5 $1 25. exf6 Bxf6 26. Rgb1 Bxc3+ 27. Kxc3 Bxb5 28. Rxb5 (28. Qxb5 $4 d4+ $19) 28... Qa4 {win10: '='} 29. Kd2 Rc8 30. Kd1 Qa1+ 31. Kd2 Qa4 $11) (23. Rb2 Ba6 24. Qf3 (24. Nb5 $1 d5 25. Nc7 Bxe2 26. Nxa8 Bc4 $15 {[%csl Ra8,Rd2,Re4,Rg4,Rh1]}) 24... Bc4 25. Rhb1 d5 26. e5 (26. exd5 $1 exd5 27. Kd1 Nc5 $17) 26... Ne4+ 27. Nxe4 dxe4 28. Qxe4 Qa5+ $19 {[%cal Gf8d8]}) 23... hxg5 24. fxg5 Nh7 25. h4 Ba6 $13 {and Black has solved all of his problems.}) (22... Qa3 $5) 23. Ra1 Rd8 ({Black will suffer after} 23... Nc5 24. Bxc5 dxc5 25. e5 Nd7 26. Rbb1 $18) 24. Ra7 $18 Qc6 {Diagram [#]} 25. Nd5 $1 {The most efficient finish! Black loses his queen.} Re8 $146 (25... exd5 26. exd5) 26. Nb4 1-0


