1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Nbd7 8. Qe2 Qc7 9. O-O-O b5 10. a3 Rb8 11. g4 (11. Nd5 {Bronstein,David 2585 - Gheorghiu,Florin 2530, Petropolis (izt) 1973 - 16/472}) 11... h6 12. Bh4 Be7 13. Bg2 b4 {Black is seeking chances on the queenside, thus reaching a highly double-edged position. Precise play is much required on both sides.} 14. axb4 Rxb4 15. Be1 Qb6 16. Bf2 Rxb2 $146 ({Much better is} 16... Qc7 17. h4 (17. Bf3 Nb6 18. Na2 Ra4 19. Kb1 d5 $13) 17... h5 18. g5 Ng4 $13 {with unclear play, as in Magshoodloo's games against Cheparinov some 10 days later.}) {Diagram [#]} 17. Ndb5 $1 Qa5 (17... Nc5 18. Kxb2 O-O (18... Nfd7 19. Bxc5 Nxc5 20. Kc1 axb5 21. Qxb5+ Nd7 22. Qxb6 Nxb6 23. h4 $18) 19. Bxc5 dxc5 20. e5 Nd7 21. Rhe1 $16) 18. Kxb2 Qb4+ 19. Kc1 axb5 {Diagram [#]} 20. Kd2 $1 {This king walk brings White some advantage.} (20. Nb1 $2 Nc5 21. c3 Qa5 $17) 20... O-O ({Black can put stronger resistance after} 20... g5 21. Rb1 Qc4 22. Rxb5 Qxe2+ 23. Nxe2 gxf4 (23... Nxg4 24. Bd4 e5 25. fxe5 dxe5 26. Bc3 $16) 24. h3 (24. Nxf4 Nxg4 25. Bg3 Bg5 26. h4 Bf6 27. Nd3 $14) 24... Ba6 25. Rb3 Bxe2 26. Kxe2 O-O 27. Rhb1 $14 {with somewhat better position for White.}) 21. Rb1 $146 ({RR} 21. Ra1 Ne5 22. Qxb5 Nc4+ 23. Kd3 Nb2+ 24. Kd2 Nc4+ 25. Kd3 Nb2+ {½-½ (25) Gutierrez Delgado,Y (2304)-Morales Marmol,M (2216) Havana 2022}) ({RR} 21. Ra1 Ne5 22. fxe5 dxe5 23. Be1 Rd8+ 24. Ke3 Nd5+ 25. Nxd5 Qd4+ 26. Kf3 exd5 27. Ba5 f5 28. Rhd1 dxe4+ 29. Kg3 f4+ 30. Kh3 h5 31. Rxd4 hxg4+ 32. Qxg4 Bxg4+ 33. Kxg4 Rxd4 34. c3 Rc4 35. Kf5 f3 {Sethuraman,S (2603)-Lim,Z (2271) Melaka 2024 1-0 (46)}) 21... Qa5 22. Rxb5 ({Probably stronger is} 22. Qxb5 Qc7 23. h3 g5 24. Ra1 gxf4 25. Ra7 Qd8 26. Rb1 $14) {Diagram [#]} 22... Qc7 $2 {The crucial mistake. Black misses the opportunity to generate some counter-chances.} ({After} 22... Qa8 23. g5 (23. h4 Ba6 24. g5 Bxb5 25. Qxb5 Rb8 26. Qe2 Nh7 27. gxh6 Qa5 $15) (23. Rg1 Ba6 24. e5 d5 $1 25. exf6 Bxf6 26. Rgb1 Bxc3+ 27. Kxc3 Bx