1. d4 {Once again following the line from the previous game.} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd2 d5 6. Nf3 b6 7. cxd5 exd5 8. Rc1 Bb7 9. Bd3 Re8 10. O-O Bf8 11. Ne5 c5 12. f4 Nc6 {Diagram [#]} 13. Ne2 $5 (13. Nxd5 $5 {At the first sight it looks winning for White, but Black has a strong counter with:} Qxd5 14. Bc4 {Diagram [#]} Qxg2+ $3 15. Kxg2 Nxe5+ 16. Kg1 Nxc4 17. Rxc4 Rad8 $1 {The attack is gone and White's king shelter is weakend. Engines confirm that Black's compensation is tangible. In fact, in my opinion it is Black who has an easier game.} 18. Qa4 a6 19. Rcc1 Re6 (19... h6 20. a3 Ne4 21. Be1 Re6 {is also good for Black as White cannot play} 22. f5 $4 {due to} Ng5 $1 $19) 20. f5 Re4 21. Rf4 Rxf4 22. exf4 Rxd4 23. Qc2 Be4 24. Qd1 Bxf5 {Black is not really down that much in material and the game is much easier for him.} 25. Qe2 Bd3 26. Qe3 Ng4 27. Qg3 Be4 28. Qxg4 Rxd2 29. f5 Rd4 30. Ra1 Bc6 31. Qg5 (31. Qh5) 31... h6 32. Qe3 Rg4+ 33. Kf1 Bd6 34. Rd1 Bxh2 35. Rd8+ Kh7 36. Qh3 Rf4+ 37. Ke2 Re4+ 38. Kd1 Be5 39. f6 Rf4 40. fxg7 Kxg7 41. Qg3+ Kf6 42. Qd3 Ke7 43. Rc8 $4 (43. Qe3) 43... Rd4 44. Qxd4 Bf3+ {0 : 1 Budisavljevic,Luka 2454 - Predke,Alexandr 2684, Srbija 2020}) 13... Rc8 {Diagram [#]} 14. Be1 $1 {Rerouting the bishop to h4 before the rook lift. Maghsoodloo lashes out the right move with high accuracy. It is possible that he might had this position analysed prior to this game.} Ne4 ({RR} 14... cxd4 15. exd4 Ne4 16. Bb5 Re6 17. h3 f6 18. Nxc6 Bxc6 19. Ba6 Rc7 20. f5 Re8 21. Nf4 Ba4 22. b3 Rxc1 23. Qxc1 Bd7 24. Nxd5 Bd6 25. Bd3 Qb8 26. Nc3 Nxc3 27. Bxc3 Bh2+ 28. Kh1 Bg3 29. Bd2 {Vidit,S (2726)-Dominguez Perez,L (2758) chess24.com INT 2021 1-0 (47)}) 15. Bxe4 dxe4 16. Nxf7 $5 Qd5 $146 {But, this is inaccurate. In the previous game we have seen how Black should play.} (16... Kxf7 17. Qb3+ c4 $1 {This was the only way to go. Maybe during the blitz game Firouzja couldn't recall all the details of this complicated line.}) ({RR} 16... Kxf7 17. Qb3+ c4 18. Qxc4+ Kg6 19. f5+ Kh6 20. Bg3 Ne5 21. Qg8 Be7 22. Rxc8 Bxc8 23. Bf4+ Bg5 24. Bxg5+ Qxg5 25. Qxe8 Qxe3+ 26. Kh1 Qxe2 27. Ra1 Qxb2 28. Rf1 Qe2 29. Ra1 Ng4 30. Qxc8 Nf2+ 31. Kg1 {Samunenkov,I (2433)-Xu,Y (2507) Chess.com INT 2022 ½-½ (36)}) ({RR} 16... Kxf7 17. Qb3+ c4 18. Qxc4+ Kg6 19. f5+ Kh6 20. Bg3 Ne5 21. Bf4+ g5 22. fxg6+ Kxg6 23. Qa4 Rxc1 24. Rxc1 Nd3 25. Rc7 Re7 26. Rxb7 Qc8 27. Rxe7 Bxe7 28. h3 a6 29. Kh2 b5 30. Qb3 Qc4 31. Qd1 {Reshetnikov,A (2492)-Bok,B (2592) Chess.com INT 2025 1-0 (41)}) ({RR} 16... Kxf7 17. Qb3+ c4 18. Qxc4+ Kg6 19. Bg3 Ne5 20. f5+ Kh6 21. Qg8 Be7 22. Qe6+ Bf6 23. Bf4+ g5 24. fxg6+ Kg7 25. Bh6+ Kxh6 26. Qh3+ Bh4 27. Ng3 hxg6 28. dxe5 Rxc1 29. Rxc1 Rxe5 30. Ne2 Ba6 31. Nd4 {Mladek,R (2436)-Hagner,B (2354) Mali Losinj 2023 0-1 (31)}) 17. Ne5 $1 {Though there were still some mistakes on both sides, I really enjoyed the way White converted this game and hope the readers would as well.} Nxe5 18. dxe5 Qxa2 (18... Qxd1 {leads to a much better endgame for White.} 19. Rxd1 Ba6 20. Kf2 $16) 19. Bc3 Qd5 $2 {The last mistake after which the game seems one sided.} (19... Red8 $1 20. Qe1 b5 $13) 20. Qe1 b5 21. Rd1 Qc4 22. b4 cxb4 23. Bd4 Rc7 24. f5 Bc8 25. e6 Qa2 26. Qg3 Rb7 27. Nf4 Bd6 28. Qg4 Bxf4 29. Qxf4 Rf8 30. Qe5 Re8 31. Rc1 Qe2 32. Rxc8 Rxc8 33. f6 Qg4 34. f7+ Kf8 35. Bc5+ Re7 36. Bxe7+ Kxe7 37. f8=R Rxf8 38. Qc5+ Kxe6 39. Qxf8 Kd5 40. Qxb4 a6 41. Qd4+ Ke6 42. Qb6+ Kd5 43. Qxa6 Qe2 44. Qb6 Kc4 45. Qd4+ 1-0


