{A09: Réti Opening: 1 Nf3 d5 2 c4} 1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 d4 3. b4 g5 4. d3 $146 (4. Qb3 Bg7 5. Nxg5 e5 6. Nh3 (6. d3 Bh6 7. f4 exf4 8. h4 Nc6 9. b5 Nce7 10. c5 Be6 11. Nxe6 fxe6 12. Qxe6 Qd5 13. Qxd5 Nxd5 14. Na3 O-O-O 15. Nc2 Ne3 16. Nxe3 fxe3 17. g4 Bf4 18. Bb2 Bg3+ 19. Kd1 Nf6 20. g5 Nh5 {Trkaljanov,V (2663)-Ciocaltea,V (2719) Sanghi Nagar 2020 200 Traps In The Opening [Rechel,B] 0-1 (39)}) 6... Ne7 7. g3 Bf5 8. Bg2 c6 9. d3 h6 10. Nd2 Nd7 11. Ne4 O-O 12. Nd6 Be6 13. Nxb7 Qc7 14. Na5 Rab8 15. Bd2 f5 16. f3 c5 17. b5 Ng6 18. Nf2 Nf6 {Duda,J (2732)-Klimkowski,J (2531) Chess.com INT 2024 0-1 (38)}) (4. Bb2 Bg7 5. Nxg5 e5 6. Ne4 f5 7. Nc5 b6 (7... Nf6 8. g3 Qe7 9. Bg2 Nbd7 10. Nd3 O-O 11. O-O c6 12. b5 c5 13. e3 e4 14. Nf4 d3 15. f3 {Roos-Dgebuadze,A Las Palmas 200 Traps In The Opening [John Watson]}) 8. Qa4+ Kf7 9. Nd3 Ne7 10. h4 Bb7 11. e3 Re8 12. Be2 Nd7 13. Na3 a5 14. b5 Be4 15. exd4 exd4 16. c5 Bxd3 17. Qb3+ Nd5 18. Qxd5+ Kf8 {Rajchovski,L-Mikanovic,S chess.com INT 2017 CBM 045 ext [Peter Wells & Richard Palliser] 0-1}) ({RR} 4. h3 h6 5. d3 Bg7 6. g3 e5 7. Nbd2 Ne7 8. Bg2 f5 9. O-O Ng6 10. Nb3 f4 11. e3 dxe3 12. fxe3 e4 13. Nfd4 f3 14. Bxf3 exf3 15. Qxf3 Ne5 16. Qh5+ Ke7 17. b5 Qe8 18. Qe2 Qg6 {Anton Guijarro,D (2693)-Sadhwani,R (2616) Warsaw 2021 1-0 (41)}) 4... g4 5. Nfd2 ({RR} 5. Nh4 e5 6. g3 Bxb4+ 7. Bd2 Be7 8. Bg2 Bxh4 9. gxh4 Qxh4 10. Na3 c6 11. c5 Be6 12. Rb1 Qe7 13. Qc2 h5 14. Nc4 Bxc4 15. Qxc4 h4 16. h3 g3 17. fxg3 hxg3 18. O-O Rh7 19. Rf3 Na6 {Muradli,M (2537)-Sadhwani,R (2628) Chess.com INT 2022 1-0 (37)}) 5... e5 6. g3 ({RR} 6. Bb2 Bxb4 7. a3 Be7 8. e3 Nc6 9. Be2 Nf6 10. Nb3 a5 11. e4 a4 12. N3d2 h5 13. Qc2 Nd7 14. f3 Nc5 15. Rf1 Be6 16. g3 h4 17. fxg4 hxg3 18. hxg3 Bg5 19. Nf3 Be3 20. Nh4 Nb3 {Vizcarra Quispe,R (1970)-Poliakova,V (2097) Lima 2025 0-1}) 6... Bxb4 $146 ({RR} 6... h5 7. Bg2 h4 8. O-O Ne7 9. Ne4 Ng6 10. f3 f5 11. fxg4 fxe4 12. Bxe4 Rg8 13. Qe1 hxg3 14. Bd5 Rg7 15. Qxg3 c6 16. Be4 Nf4 17. Rxf4 exf4 18. Bxf4 Bxg4 19. Be5 Qg5 20. Na3 Be6 21. Bxg7 {Czebe,A (2418)-Stupak,K (2542) Chennai 2019 0-1 (36)}) 7. Bg2 {Hoping for Qa4+.} Nc6 8. O-O {Black is slightly better.} Be7 9. Nb3 f5 10. e3 dxe3 11. Bxe3 Nf6 12. Nc3 O-O 13. d4 e4 $1 14. Bf4 {[%eval -82,22]} ({White should play} 14. Qc1 $15 {[%eval -32,23]}) 14... Nh5 15. Bh6 {[#]} Rf7 16. Qd2 Bf8 17. Be3 {[%eval -106,23]} (17. a4 $15 {[%eval -51,21]}) 17... Bg7 {[%eval -61,22]} (17... b6 $17 {[%eval -106,23]} 18. Bh6 Ba6 19. Bxf8 Qxf8) 18. Rad1 Nf6 {[%eval -38,21]} (18... b6 $17 {[%eval -87,22]}) 19. Ne2 {[%eval -74,21] [#]} (19. Qc1 $15 {[%eval -38,21]}) 19... a5 {[%eval -2,20]} ({Better is} 19... Nh5 $1 $17 {[%eval -74,21]}) 20. a4 {[%eval -67,21]} (20. Nf4 $1 $11 {[%eval -2,20]}) 20... Nh5 21. Qc1 Qe8 {[%eval -56,24] &Nero is more active.} (21... Qf6 $17 {[%eval -108,21]} 22. d5 Nb4) 22. Nf4 {[%eval -189,22]} ({White should try} 22. Rfe1 $15 {[%eval -56,24]}) 22... Nxf4 $19 23. Bxf4 Nb4 24. d5 {[%eval -271,20]} (24. Qe3 {[%eval -191,22] might work better.}) 24... Qxa4 25. Nc5 Qe8 26. h3 {[%eval -311,22]} (26. Rfe1 $142 {[%eval -167,23]}) 26... b6 $2 {[%eval -108,20]} (26... gxh3 $19 {[%eval -311,22] has better winning chances.} 27. Bxh3 b6) 27. Ne6 $17 gxh3 (27... Bxe6 {looks sharper.} 28. dxe6 Qxe6 29. hxg4 Re7) 28. Bxh3 {[%eval -305,20]} (28. Nxg7 $17 {[%eval -75,23]} Rxg7 29. Bxh3) 28... Bxe6 $19 29. dxe6 Qxe6 30. Qe3 Re8 31. Rd2 Nd3 32. Rfd1 Nxf4 33. Qxf4 Bh6 {Black is clearly winning.} 34. Qh4 Bxd2 35. Rxd2 e3 36. Re2 exf2+ 37. Rxf2 Qf6 38. Qh5 Qg6 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.48/Black=0.25 (precise)} 0-1


