{[%evp 0,74,36,23,49,49,54,22,22,19,22,19,19,19,19,19,26,26,26,27,27,27,33,27,30,24,55,0,0,0,3,3,10,10,10,10,8,-58,10,10,22,20,20,11,11,20,21,21,37,49,52,52,93,93,93,93,133,133,137,137,145,134,134,191,182,182,230,189,272,245,387,399,896,896,892,904,1450] Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'B33: Sicilian: Pelikan and Sveshnikov Variations'} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Nd5 Nxd5 8. exd5 Ne7 (8... Nb8 {See 8...b8 games. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'See 8...Nb8 games.'}) 9. c4 Nf5 (9... Ng6 {See 9...g6 game. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'See 9...Ng6 game.'}) 10. Bd3 g6 (10... Be7 11. O-O O-O (11... a6 12. Nc3 O-O {Transposes to 11...0-0.}) 12. f4 $1 a6 (12... g6 13. Kh1 {A nice prophylactic move to prevent tactics with Black's ...b6+. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'A nice prophylactic move to prevent tactics with Black's ...Qb6+.'} a6 14. Nc3 $16 {Kuusela,M (2226)-Satosuo,R (2010) ICCF email 2014}) (12... Qb6+ {Black intends to play ...e3 and force the exchange with the dark-squared bishop, but White gets a better position in the end. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Black intends to play ...Ne3 and force the exchange with the dark-squared bishop, but White gets a better position in the end.'} 13. Kh1 a6 (13... Ne3 $6 14. Bxe3 Qxe3 15. Qc2 $1 g6 16. Rf3 Qc5 17. f5 $18 {White has a decisive advantage.}) 14. Nc3 Ne3 15. Bxe3 Qxe3 16. f5 $16 {Tarlev,K (2568)-Pyrig,R (1927) Lichess.org INT 2021}) 13. Nc3 exf4 14. Bxf4 Nh4 15. Qc2 Ng6 16. Be3 Bd7 17. Bd4 Rc8 {(Kholmov,R (2555)-Gurgenidze,B (2510) Tbilisi 1977)} 18. b3 $14) 11. O-O a6 12. Nc3 Bg7 13. Bxf5 Bxf5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'White is slightly better.'} 14. Be3 Rc8 (14... O-O {was tried by Fedoseev against Shirov, where Shirov misplaced his queen on b3, but eventually was still able to defeat Black.} 15. Qd2 Qh4 16. b3 e4 17. Bd4 (17. Ne2 $5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH}) 17... Bh6 $1 18. Qe1 $14) 15. Qa4+ Qd7 16. Qxd7+ {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'N'} (16. Rac1 {is even better.} Bf6 (16... Bd3 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH} 17. Qxd7+ Kxd7 18. Rfd1 Bxc4 19. Na4 {[%eval 32760,0] Nc6 Sveshnikov-Sveshnikov 8...Ne7}) 17. Qb4 {Avoiding the queens exchange for the moment.} Bd3 18. Na4 $1 {A surprise move. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Nb6 would now be deadly. A surprise move.'} Bd8 (18... Bxf1 19. Nb6 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '!'} Qg4 {The only move to keep fighting.} 20. Rxf1 $1 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'And now h3! would win.'} Rd8 21. f3 Qf5 22. c5 O-O $1 (22... dxc5 $6 {[%eval 189,22] Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '22... 0-0 0.74'} 23. Bxc5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Strongly threatening Qa4+.'} Qd3 24. f4 Qb5 25. Re1 Qxb4 26. Bxb4 $18 {Black's rook on h8 is completely out of play at the moment and with the king on the center and exposed, White is clearly better.}) 23. c6 Qd3 $1 24. Qb3 Qxb3 25. axb3 bxc6 26. dxc6 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Threatens to win with Ra1.'} e4 27. c7 Rc8 {Black has no other good choice.} 28. Nd5 Bxb2 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '[#]'} 29. Rf2 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '!'} Bg7 30. Ne7+ Kh8 31. Rc2 $1 $14 {White's attack is very promissing and it's very easy for Black to go wrong in this line.})) 16... Bxd7 17. Ne4 Bf8 $1 18. f4 $146 {[%eval -27,23]} (18. Rfc1 {instead.}) ({White should play} 18. Nd2 $14 {[%eval 31,23] Szabo,Krisztian, MH}) ({RR} 18. Rac1 f5 19. Nf6+ Ke7 20. Nxd7 Kxd7 21. b4 Be7 22. f3 Ra8 23. Rc2 a5 24. b5 Bh4 25. g3 Bd8 26. b6 Rf8 27. Kg2 g5 28. Bg1 Be7 29. Re1 a4 30. c5 dxc5 31. Rxe5 Ra6 32. Rxe7+ Kxe7 {Du,Y (2008)-Guo,H (2086) Nanjing/Beijing 2025 1-0 (40)}) 18... f5 {Allows White to recover.} (18... Bf5 {And Black is at least equal. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '!'}) 19. Nf6+ Ke7 20. fxe5 dxe5 21. Nxd7 Kxd7 22. Rac1 Bg7 $2 {[%eval 100,20] Black misreads the position and wrongly assumes the bishop is better on g7. From here, Black falls very fast.} (22... Bc5 {[%eval 20,18] Trading bishops was a way to keep a balanced position. At least, 22...Be7, so Black could have more control on the a3-f8 diagonal and delay the White's queenside pawns advance. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '=' Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'remains equal.'} 23. Bxc5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH} Rxc5) 23. b4 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '' Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'White is more active. Black is on the road to losing.'} f4 24. Bb6 Rhf8 $6 {[%eval 246,20]} (24... Bf6 $16 {[%eval 130,17] Szabo,Krisztian, MH}) 25. c5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '+-'} e4 {[%eval 305,21] Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '[#]'} (25... Rf6 $142 {[%eval 204,19] Szabo,Krisztian, MH} 26. a4 Bh6 (26... e4 $2 27. Rfd1 $18)) 26. c6+ {White pawns are too fast. Szabo,Krisztian, MH: '!'} bxc6 27. dxc6+ Ke6 {[%eval 347,25]} ({Much worse is} 27... Rxc6 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH} 28. Rfd1+ Rd6 29. Rc7+ Ke6 30. Rxd6+ Kxd6 31. Rxg7 $18) (27... Ke8 {[%eval 229,19] (Szabo,Krisztian, MH) keeps fighting.} 28. a4 (28. Rc4 Rf6 $16) 28... Rf6) 28. Rfd1 e3 29. c7 Bf6 30. a4 Rfe8 31. Kf1 Kf5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'aiming for ...e2+.'} 32. Ke2 Re4 33. Ba5 Be7 34. Kf3 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Hoping for Rd5+.'} Re6 {[%eval 601,21]} (34... Re5 $142 {[%eval 416,20] Szabo,Krisztian, MH} 35. Rd8 Bxd8 36. cxd8=Q Rxd8 37. Bxd8 e2) 35. Rd5+ {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'White is clearly winning.'} Re5 36. Rxe5+ Kxe5 37. b5 Kd5 {Szabo,Krisztian, MH: 'Weighted Error Value: White=0.07 (flawless) /Black=0.49. Mistake:    White=1   Black=5   Inaccurate:   ---    Black=2 OK:     White=18   Black=5   Best:     ---    Black=3'} 1-0


