{C00: French: Unusual White 2nd moves} 1. e4 e6 2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 exd5 4. Qb3 (4. exd5 Nf6 5. Bb5+ Nbd7 6. Nc3 Be7 7. d4 O-O 8. Nge2 Nb6 9. Qb3 Nfxd5 10. O-O Be6 11. Nxd5 Qxd5 12. Qxd5 Nxd5 13. Nf4 Nxf4 14. Bxf4 c6 15. Be2 Rfd8 16. Rfd1 Rd7 17. Be3 Rad8 18. d5 Rxd5 {Capoccia,A-Lemaire,P IECG email 2007 The S African Chessplaye [Sale,Srdjan] 0-1 (50)}) 4... Nf6 $146 (4... dxe4 5. Bc4 Qe7 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. d3 Nbd7 8. Be3 Ne5 9. dxe4 Qb4 10. Bb5+ c6 11. Qxb4 Bxb4 12. Bd4 cxb5 13. Bxe5 Nxe4 14. Nge2 O-O 15. O-O Nxc3 16. Nxc3 Be6 17. Rfd1 a6 18. a4 bxa4 19. Nxa4 {Schmidt,O-7.d2 a5 8.ab5 c3_60652 Basel 1988 Lexikon04 [Dragan Solak] 0-1 (51)} Rad8 20. h3 Bb3 21. Rdc1 Rfe8 22. Bf4 Rc8 23. Nb6 Rxc1+ 24. Rxc1 Re1+ 25. Rxe1 Bxe1 26. Be3 Bb4 27. Kf1 Kf8 28. Ke2 Ke7 29. Kd3 Kd6 30. Nc4+ Bxc4+ 31. Kxc4 Ba5 32. Bc5+ Kc6 33. b4 Bc7 34. Bd4 {Schmied,R-7.d2 a5 8.ab5 c3_60652 Barcelona 1987 ZUS C73 [Sverre Eugen Olsen] 0-1 (51)} g6 35. Bc3 b6 36. g4 a5 37. bxa5 bxa5 38. f3 Bd8 39. Bd2 Kd6 40. Kb5 Kd5 41. Be3 Ke5 42. Ka4 f5 43. gxf5 Kxf5 44. Bd2 Bg5 45. Bxa5 Be3 46. Bc7 Bd4 47. Kb5 Be5 48. Bd8 Kf4 49. Kc6 {Richter,L-Peluso,A corr ICCF 1987 UltraCorr3a [RK] 0-1 (51)}) 5. Nc3 ({RR} 5. e5 Ne4 6. Nc3 Nxc3 7. dxc3 Be7 8. f4 O-O 9. Be3 c5 10. O-O-O Be6 11. Qc2 Qd7 12. Bd3 g6 13. h3 f5 14. Nf3 Nc6 15. g4 Rad8 16. Rdg1 d4 17. gxf5 Bxf5 18. Bxf5 Rxf5 19. cxd4 cxd4 {Gressmann,M (2122)-Zavortink,M (2135) Chess.com INT 2025 1-0}) 5... d4 6. Bc4 dxc3 $146 {[%eval 14,20]} (6... Qd7 $15 {[%eval -40,17]} 7. Nd5 Nxe4) ({RR} 6... Qe7 7. Nb5 Nxe4 8. Ne2 Nc5 9. Qg3 d3 10. O-O dxe2 11. Re1 Nba6 12. Rxe2 Ne6 13. d4 c6 14. Bg5 Qd7 15. d5 cxd5 16. Rd1 Qc6 17. Bxd5 Qxb5 18. Bc6+ {1-0 (18) Hess,M (2441)-Fica Cruz,J (1949) Tornelo INT 2021}) ({RR} 6... Qd7 7. e5 Ng4 8. e6 fxe6 9. Ne4 Ne5 10. Nf3 Nxc4 11. Qxc4 Nc6 12. O-O Qd5 13. Qe2 Be7 14. d3 O-O 15. Bg5 e5 16. Bxe7 Nxe7 17. Rac1 Bg4 18. Rxc7 Bxf3 19. gxf3 Ng6 20. Kh1 Nf4 21. Rg1 {Shevchenko,K (2599)-Rychagov,A (2545) Chess.com INT 2020 1-0}) ({RR} 6... Qd7 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Nd5 Nxd5 9. Bxd5 Na5 10. Qd3 Bd6 11. Qxd4 O-O 12. b4 Nc6 13. Bxc6 Qxc6 14. Bb2 f6 15. O-O Bg4 16. Rac1 Qb5 17. Nh4 Be5 18. Qe3 Bxb2 19. Rxc7 Be5 20. Re7 Qxb4 21. Qb3+ {Shevchenko,K (2599)-Stromboli,E (2308) Chess.com INT 2021 ½-½ (58)}) 7. Bxf7+ $11 Ke7 8. bxc3 {[%eval 0,19]} (8. e5 $14 {[%eval 39,19]} Ne4 9. bxc3) 8... c5 {[%eval 101,20]} (8... Nxe4 $11 {[%eval 0,19]} 9. Nf3 Nd6) 9. e5 $1 $16 {White has strong compensation.} Ne4 {[%eval 151,19]} (9... Nc6 $142 {[%eval 110,19]} 10. Nf3 (10. exf6+ Kxf6 11. Ne2 Na5 $14) 10... Na5 11. exf6+ Kxf6) 10. d4 {[%eval 90,18]} (10. Bd5 $142 {[%eval 151,19]} Ng5 11. d4 (11. Bxb7 Bxb7 12. Qxb7+ Nd7 $16)) 10... Qb6 {[#]} 11. Qd5 {[%eval 70,20]} (11. Ne2 $1 $16 {[%eval 108,20]}) 11... Qc6 {[%eval 117,19]} ({Black should try} 11... Na6 $14 {[%eval 70,20]}) 12. Nf3 $2 {[%eval -157,19]} (12. Ne2 $16 {[%eval 117,19] is necessary to keep the advantage.}) 12... Qxd5 $17 13. Bxd5 Nxc3 14. Bg5+ Kd7 {[%eval -90,19]} (14... Ke8 $142 {[%eval -152,20]} 15. Bb3 cxd4 16. Nxd4 Ne4) 15. e6+ {[%eval -179,19]} (15. Bf7 $17 {[%eval -90,19] keeps fighting.} Nc6 16. d5) 15... Kd6 16. Bc4 {[%eval -246,19] [#]} (16. Bb3 {[%eval -167,20] was forced.} cxd4 17. Nxd4) 16... Bxe6 $2 {[%eval 69,21]} ({Better is} 16... cxd4 $1 $19 {[%eval -246,19]} 17. Nxd4 Kc5) 17. Bf4+ $2 {[%eval -277,21] White does not recover from this.} (17. dxc5+ $14 {[%eval 69,21] was the only good move.} Kd7 18. Ne5+ Kc7 19. Bxe6 Bxc5 20. Rc1) 17... Ke7 $19 18. Bg5+ Kd7 19. Ne5+ Kd6 20. O-O $2 {[%eval -437,20]} (20. dxc5+ {[%eval -264,19] might work better.} Kxe5 21. f4+ Kd4 22. Bxe6) 20... cxd4 {aiming for ...Bxc4.} 21. Bf4 {[%eval -805,19]} (21. Bxe6 $142 {[%eval -473,18]} Kxe6 22. Rfe1) 21... Bxc4 22. Nxc4+ Kc5 23. Ne5 Nc6 24. Nf7 Rg8 {...Ne2+ is the strong threat.} 25. Ng5 Kd5 {Hoping for ...Ne2+.} 26. Rfe1 Bc5 27. Re6 Rae8 28. Rxe8 Rxe8 29. h4 h6 30. Nf3 Ne2+ 31. Kh2 Nxf4 32. Rb1 Bb6 33. g3 Ne6 34. Kg1 Nc5 35. Rd1 d3 36. Kf1 Re2 37. Nd2 Nd4 {White must now prevent ...Ba5.} 38. Nb1 Ne4 39. Rxd3 Rxf2+ 40. Ke1 Ke5 41. Re3 Ba5+ {[%eval -1734,5]} (41... Nc2+ $142 {[%eval -32759,10]} 42. Kd1 Nxe3+ 43. Ke1 Ba5+ 44. Nd2 Bxd2#) 42. Kd1 Rf1+ {Weighted Error Value: White=1.21/Black=0.74} 0-1


