1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Bg5 dxc4 5. Qa4+ Nbd7 6. Qxc4 a6 {I suggest to start with 6...c5, but this is also fine.} 7. Nbd2 c5 8. dxc5 ({RR} 8. Qc2 b5 9. a4 Bb7 10. e3 cxd4 11. axb5 dxe3 12. Bxe3 axb5 13. Rxa8 Qxa8 14. Bxb5 Qa1+ 15. Qb1 Qa5 16. Bxd7+ Nxd7 17. O-O Be7 18. Nc4 Qb4 19. b3 Bxf3 20. gxf3 O-O 21. Rc1 Nf6 22. Qd3 Nd5 {Laurusas,T (2579)-Cernousek,L (2430) Slovakia 2025 ½-½ (47)}) 8... Bxc5 {Black has a great game.} 9. Ne4 b5 $1 10. Qd3 $146 ({RR} 10. Qb3 Bb7 11. Nxc5 Nxc5 12. Qa3 Rc8 13. Rd1 Qb6 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Qb4 Na4 16. e3 Qc5 17. Qxc5 Rxc5 18. b3 Nc3 19. Rc1 b4 20. Nd2 Ke7 21. f3 Rhc8 22. Rc2 f5 23. Nc4 a5 24. a3 Nd5 {Utegaliev,A (2473)-Kostenko,P (2374) Semey 2022 0-1 (60)}) ({RR} 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. Qc3 Be7 12. g3 Bb7 13. Ned2 Rc8 14. Qb3 Qa5 15. a3 Ne5 16. Bg2 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 O-O 18. Qd1 Rfd8 19. b4 Qc7 20. Ra2 Nc4 21. e3 Rd3 22. Qe2 Nxd2 23. Rxd2 Qc1+ 24. Qd1 Qxd1+ {Dreev,A (2677)-Inarkiev,E (2663) Moscow 2019 ½-½ (74)}) ({RR} 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. Qc3 Qe7 12. Nxc5 Qxc5 13. Qxc5 Nxc5 14. Rc1 Na4 15. b3 Nb6 16. g3 Bb7 17. Bg2 O-O 18. O-O Rac8 19. Nd4 Bxg2 20. Kxg2 Nd5 21. Nc6 f5 22. Rc2 Rc7 23. Rfc1 Kg7 24. Kf3 Rfc8 {Kalinitschew,S (2485)-Paulsen,D (2382) Berlin 2002 1-0 (44)}) 10... Bb4+ {A clever intermediate move, forcing one of White's pieces to retreat.} 11. Bd2 Bxd2+ 12. Nfxd2 O-O $17 {Black has overtaken White in development.} 13. g3 Nxe4 14. Nxe4 (14. Qxe4 Rb8 15. Qe3 Bb7 16. f3 Nf6) 14... Bb7 15. Bg2 f5 $1 {The most energetic and best move!} 16. Nf6+ Qxf6 17. Bxb7 Nc5 18. Qf3 Qxb2 19. O-O Nxb7 ({Best was} 19... Rab8 $1 20. Bc6 Rfc8 21. Rac1 Qe5 $17 {[%csl Rc6][%cal Gc8c7,Gb8c8] when White has problems with his bishop.}) 20. Qxb7 Qxe2 21. Rfe1 Qb2 22. Rad1 f4 23. gxf4 Rae8 24. Re4 Qxa2 25. Rd7 Kh8 26. Kg2 Qc2 27. Rxg7 Rg8 28. Rg3 Rb8 29. Rxg8+ Rxg8+ 30. Kf3 Qd1+ 31. Ke3 Rd8 0-1


