1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bf5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Nh4 Bg6 7. Nxg6 hxg6 8. Bd3 Nbd7 9. O-O {Transposing to a position which can arise via the 5.d3 move order.} (9. Qe2) 9... Bd6 10. h3 dxc4 $6 11. Bxc4 Nb6 12. Bb3 {White has achieved an ideal setup.} e5 13. Qc2 (13. dxe5 Bxe5 14. Qf3 O-O 15. Rd1 Qe7 16. Bd2) (13. Qf3 Qe7) 13... Qe7 (13... exd4 14. exd4 Bc7 15. Bg5 Kf8 (15... Qd6 16. f4 Qxd4+ 17. Rf2) 16. Qd3 Qd6 17. f4 Nbd5 18. Rae1) 14. Bd2 (14. f4 exd4 15. exd4 O-O-O 16. f5 Bc7 17. fxg6 fxg6 18. Qxg6 Rxd4 19. Qf7 Qxf7 (19... Qe5 20. Qe6+) 20. Bxf7) 14... O-O-O 15. d5 $1 (15. Nb5 Bb8 16. a4 (16. Rac1 e4) 16... Nbd5) 15... e4 (15... c5 16. e4) 16. dxc6 Qe5 (16... Rxh3 17. gxh3 Qe5 18. f4 exf3 19. Rxf3 Qh2+ 20. Kf1 Qh1+ 21. Ke2 Qg2+ 22. Rf2 Qxh3 23. Raf1) 17. f4 exf3 18. Rxf3 Ng4 (18... Qh2+ 19. Kf2 Bb4 20. Bxf7 (20. Be1 Rhe8 21. Rxf6 gxf6 22. Bxf7 Re5 23. Bxg6 Bc5) 20... Rxd2+ 21. Qxd2 Bxc3 (21... Ne4+ 22. Nxe4 Bxd2 23. cxb7+ Kb8 24. Nxd2 Qd6 25. Nc4 Nxc4 26. Bxc4) 22. Qd3 Rd8 23. cxb7+ Kxb7 24. Qxd8 Ne4+ 25. Ke2 Qxg2+ 26. Kd3 Nc5+ (26... Qd2+ 27. Kxe4 Qxd8 28. bxc3 Nd7) 27. Kxc3 Nba4+ 28. Kb4 Qxb2+ 29. Bb3 Qc3+ 30. Ka3 Qb2+) 19. cxb7+ $1 Kb8 20. hxg4 Rh1+ 21. Kf2 Rxa1 22. Ne2 Bc5 (22... Rd7 23. Nd4 Qh2) 23. Bc3 $2 (23. Rxf7 Rxd2 24. Qxd2 Bxe3+ 25. Qxe3 Rf1+ 26. Kxf1 Qxe3) (23. Nd4 Rxd4 (23... Bxd4 24. exd4 Qxd4+ 25. Be3 Qb4 26. Rxf7 Qe1+ 27. Kf3 Qf1+ 28. Ke4 Re8+ 29. Kd4 Rd1+ (29... Rd8+ 30. Kc5 Nd7+ 31. Kb4 Qe1+ 32. Bd2) 30. Qxd1 Qxf7 31. Bxf7 Rd8+ 32. Kc5 Rxd1 33. Kc6 Rf1 34. Bc5 Rc1 35. b4 Na4) 24. exd4 Bxd4+ 25. Be3 Bxe3+ 26. Rxe3 Qf4+ 27. Rf3 Qd4+ 28. Re3) (23. Bxf7 Qe7) 23... Qe7 $1 24. g5 $2 {Now the game descends into chaos from which Magnus eventually emerges victorious, but it has nothing to do with the opening!} Rdd1 (24... Qxg5 25. Qe4 f5 26. Qf4+ Qxf4 27. Nxf4 Kxb7 28. Ne6 Rc8 29. Rg3) (24... Rd7 25. Bxf7 (25. Bxg7 Qxg5 26. Qe4 f5) 25... Bxe3+ (25... Rdd1 26. Qxg6 Rf1+ 27. Kg3 Rxf3+ 28. gxf3 Qxe3 29. Qe4 Qxg5+ 30. Qg4 Bd6+ 31. Kg2 Qh6 32. Bh5) 26. Rxe3 Qxf7+ 27. Rf3 Qe7 28. Qxg6 Na4 29. Bxg7 Nc5 30. Bf8 Ne4+ 31. Ke3 Qxg5+ 32. Qxg5 Nxg5 33. Rf5 Ne6) 25. Ng3 Bd6 26. Qe2 (26. Ne4 Rac1 27. Qe2 Rf1+) 26... Rg1 $146 (26... Bxg3+ 27. Rxg3 Rf1+ 28. Qxf1 Rxf1+ 29. Kxf1 Nd7 30. Bxg7 (30. Rf3 Ne5 31. Bd5 Nxf3 32. Bxf3 Qxe3 33. Bxg7 Qxg5) 30... Nc5 31. Bc2 Ne4 (31... Qe6) 32. Bxe4 Qxe4 33. a3) ({RR} 26... Bxg3+ 27. Rxg3 Rf1+ 28. Qxf1 Rxf1+ 29. Kxf1 Nd7 30. Bxg7 Nc5 {½-½ (30) Hajnal,Z (2401)-Galyas,M (2403) Kecskemet 2012}) 27. Qd3 (27. Qb5) 27... Bc7 28. Ne4 Raf1+ $1 29. Ke2 $2 Rxf3 30. gxf3 f5 $2 (30... Be5 31. Bxf7 Bxc3 32. bxc3) (30... Rg2+ 31. Kf1 (31. Kd1 Rg1+ 32. Kc2 Rg2+) 31... Rh2 32. f4 f5 (32... Qf8 33. Nf2 Qh8 34. Bxf7 Qh4 35. Be1) 33. gxf6 gxf6 34. Bxf6 (34. Nxf6 Rh3) 34... Qh7 (34... Rh1+ 35. Ke2 (35. Kg2 Qh7 36. Nf2 Qh2+ 37. Kf3 Qh5+) 35... Rh2+ 36. Kf3 Qh7 37. Be6 g5) 35. Nf2 Nd7 36. Bd4 Qh4 37. Qe2 Qg3 38. Bd5 Nb6 39. Bc6 Nc4 40. b3 Na5 (40... Nd6 41. Qf3 Qh4 42. Kg1) 41. Bd5 Nxb7 42. Qf3 Qxf3 43. Bxf3) 31. gxf6 gxf6 32. Bxf6 $2 Qh7 33. Qb5 Rg2+ (33... Nd7 34. Bd4 Qh3 (34... Qh1 35. Nf2) 35. Kd2 Qg2+ 36. Kc3 Rc1+ 37. Kb4) (33... a6 34. Qe8+ Kxb7 35. Nc5+ Ka7 36. Qc6 Qh2+ 37. Kd3 Qd6+ 38. Qxd6 Bxd6) 34. Kd3 Qd7+ (34... Nd7 $11 {was fine for Black in V. Dzhangobegov - A.Timofeev, Sochi 2016 (1/2-1/2 in 64).} 35. Be6) (34... a6 35. Qe8+ Kxb7 36. Nc5+ Ka7 37. Qc6 g5+ 38. e4 Bf4 39. Bd4) 35. Qxd7 $1 Nxd7 $2 36. Bd5 Be5 $4 (36... Nxf6 37. Nxf6 a5 $11 {B.Spassky - B.Gulko, Linares 1990 (1/2-1/ 2 in 38).} 38. Nd7+ Ka7 39. e4 Rxb2 40. e5) 37. f4 (37. Bxe5+ $16 {Black could have tried} Nxe5+ $14 38. Kd4 Nd7 (38... Nxf3+ 39. Kc3) 39. Bc6 $132 {was a better attempt.} Rg1 {has been tested a lot, including the following classic.} 40. Nf2) 37... Bc7 (37... Bxf6 38. Nxf6 $19 Nc5+ $18 39. Kd4 $11 Rc2 $19 40. b4 $11 Nxb7 $1 $19 41. Nd7+ $14 {The strongest move was counter-intuitive, freeing the f5-square for the black knight:} Kc7 $1 42. Nf8) 38. Bc6 $4 1-0


