1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 ({We start with an English. A more 'official' move order would be} 2... g6 3. d4 ({or} 3. b3 Bg7 4. Bb2 O-O 5. g3 d6 6. Bg2 c5 7. d4 d5) 3... Bg7 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. b3 c5 7. Bb2 d5) 3. b3 g6 4. Bb2 Bg7 5. g3 (5. e3 {- 138/(18)}) 5... O-O 6. Bg2 d6 7. d4 {Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Diagram [#]'} d5 $5 {An interesting move which is seen in some similar lines. Really the move orders and transpositions are quite tricky. Petronijevic,Zoran: '?!' An interesting move which is seen in some similar lines. Really the move orders and transpositions are quite tricky.} ({For} 7... Ne4 8. O-O Nc6 {see Kramnik,V (2803)-Kavutskiy,K (2390) Douglas 2017}) (7... Qa5+ $5 8. Bc3 (8. Nc3 Ne4 9. Rc1 Nc6 10. O-O Bf5 {looks ok for Black}) 8... Qc7) (7... Nc6 8. d5 (8. O-O {transposes to an English Opening of some sort}) 8... Na5 9. O-O {is like a Yugoslav.}) 8. dxc5 {The alternatives are more common:} (8. cxd5 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '- 32/(652)'} Nxd5 9. Qd2 ({the similar} 9. O-O Nc6 10. Qd2 {is covered this month in Lye,L (2377)-Moussard,J (2598) Karlsruhe 2019 is covered this month in Lye,L (2377)-Moussard,J (2598) Karlsruhe 2019}) 9... Nc7 {see Stocek,J (2545) -Gallagher,J (2522) Plovdiv BUL 2003 see Stocek,J (2545) -Gallagher,J (2522) Plovdiv BUL 2003}) (8. O-O {gives Black some choice:} dxc4 (8... cxd4) (8... Nc6) 9. bxc4 {is actually a Grunfeld! For example, 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 c6 4.Bg2 d5 5.Nf3 Bg7 6.0-0 0-0 7.b3 dxc4 8.bxc4 c5 9.Bb2. is actually a Grunfeld! For example, 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 c6 4.Bg2 d5 5.Nf3 Bg7 6.0-0 0-0 7.b3 dxc4 8.bxc4 c5 9.Bb2.}) 8... dxc4 (8... Qa5+ 9. Nbd2 $14) 9. Nbd2 {White should develop.} (9. O-O Na6 (9... cxb3 $6 10. axb3) 10. Nbd2 Nxc5 11. Nxc4 {transposes}) (9. Qxd8 $6 Rxd8 10. bxc4 Na6 $15) 9... Na6 {And the same goes for Black.} (9... cxb3 10. axb3 $14 {White can hold the c5-pawn. White can hold the c5-pawn.} Na6 11. Qc1 $14) ({RR} 9... Qa5 10. O-O c3 11. Nc4 Qxc5 12. Bxc3 Nc6 13. Rc1 Bf5 14. Ne3 Rfd8 15. Nd2 Qb5 16. a4 Qb6 17. Nxf5 gxf5 18. Qc2 Nd4 19. Bxd4 Qxd4 20. Rfd1 Qb4 21. Qc4 Rd4 22. Qxb4 Rxb4 23. Rc4 Rb6 24. Rdc1 {Rodriguez Vila,A (2460)-Casalaspro,M (2310) Buenos Aires 2025 1-0 (61)}) 10. O-O (10. Nxc4 $5) 10... Nxc5 (10... cxb3 11. Nxb3 $14) 11. Nxc4 {transposes} Be6 {In a symmetrical position, White would have a little something - if he can create some initiative. In a symmetrical position, White would have a little something - if he can create some initiative.} 12. Qc1 $146 {Gawain had been down this road before. Petronijevic,Zoran: 'N'} (12. Rc1 Bh6 $5 (12... Rc8) 13. Ra1 {well...} (13. Rc2 $2 Qxd1 14. Rxd1 Bf5 $17) (13. Ncd2 $5) 13... Rc8 (13... Bg7) 14. Nfe5 Qc7 15. e3 Rfd8 {Black has certainly equalized Black has certainly equalized} 16. Qe2 Bd5 17. Rfd1 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Bg7 19. Rac1 Rxd1 20. Rxd1 Nfd7 21. Nxd7 Nxd7 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. Qb2+ Nf6 24. a4 Rd8 25. Rxd8 {1/2-1/2 Howell,D (2696)-Jones,G (2682) London 2018}) ({RR} 12. Rc1 Bh6 13. Ra1 Rc8 14. Nfe5 Qc7 15. e3 Rfd8 16. Qe2 Bd5 17. Rfd1 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Bg7 19. Rac1 Rxd1 20. Rxd1 Nfd7 21. Nxd7 Nxd7 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. Qb2+ Nf6 24. a4 Rd8 25. Rxd8 {½-½ (25) Howell,D (2696)-Jones,G (2682) London 2018}) 12... Rc8 13. Rd1 Qe8 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '='} 14. Qf4 (14. Bd4 Bxc4 15. Qxc4 Ne6 16. Qb4 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 $11) 14... Nce4 $6 ({Black could solve his problems concretely with} 14... Bxc4 $1 15. Qxc4 Nce4 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '='} 16. Qb4 {as now there is a nice shot:} (16. Qd4 Rc2 $132) 16... Nc3 $1 $11 {If} 17. Bxc3 (17. Rd2 $6 Nfe4 $132) (17. Re1 b6 $11) 17... Nd5 $1 18. Qxb7 (18. Rxd5 $2 Bxc3) 18... Nxc3 19. Re1 Nxe2+ $1 20. Rxe2 Bxa1 21. Rxe7 {when White will probably have enough for the exchange, but nothing more}) 15. Nfe5 $14 {White has some edge with the more active pieces.} b5 16. Na5 {Petronijevic,Zoran: ''} Rc2 17. Bd4 (17. Bxe4 Nxe4 18. Qxe4 Rxb2 19. Nac6 $14) 17... Bd5 18. Qe3 Qa8 19. Bh3 $6 ({It was best to first play} 19. f3 $1 Nd6 {and then} 20. Bh3 $14 (20. Qd3 Rfc8 21. Bh3 e6 22. Nac4 $14)) 19... h6 $1 {Black's knight reaches the annoying g5-square, where it creates threats against White's king and can also go to e6. Black's knight reaches the annoying g5-square, where it creates threats against White's king and can also go to e6.} 20. Rdc1 Ng5 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '?' Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Diagram [#]'} (20... Rxc1+ $1 21. Rxc1 Ng5 $13) 21. Bf1 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '?'} (21. Rxc2 Nxh3+ 22. Kf1 Bxb3 23. Rc6 Bd5 24. Rac1 Ng5 25. f3 $16) 21... Rfc8 {Petronijevic,Zoran: ''} 22. Rxc2 Rxc2 23. Rc1 Qc8 24. Nac6 $2 {This is very natural, but it could have run into an unexpected shot. This is very natural, but it could have run into an unexpected shot.} (24. Rxc2 $142 Qxc2 25. Qd3 Qc1 26. Nf3 Nh3+ 27. Kg2 e5 28. Bxe5 Nxf2 29. Kxf2 Ng4+ 30. Kg1 Bxe5 31. Qxd5 Qe3+ 32. Kh1 Qc1 33. Kg1 Ne3 34. Qd8+ Kg7 35. Kf2 $11) 24... Rxc1 $2 ({According to the live broadcast, Gawain spent less than a minute here. Black had the opportunity to play According to the live broadcast, Gawain spent less than a minute here. Black had the opportunity to play} 24... Nh3+ $1 25. Bxh3 Qxh3 {with the incredible point with the incredible point} 26. f3 (26. Nxe7+ Kh7 27. Nxd5 (27. Nf3 Ng4 $19) 27... Nxd5 {wins material academically} 28. Rxc2 Nxe3 29. fxe3 Bxe5 30. Bxe5 Qf5 31. Rc5 g5 $19 (31... Qh5 $19)) 26... Ng4 $3 27. Nxg4 Bxf3 $3 $19) 25. Qxc1 Kh7 26. f3 $2 {Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Diagram [#]'} ({White regains control with White regains control with} 26. Qc5 $14 {with one point being that} Ne6 {can be met with} 27. Bh3 $1 Bxc6 28. Nxc6 a6 29. e3 Ne4 30. Qd5 $14) 26... Nd7 $1 {All of a sudden White's cluster of pieces in the centre are in trouble All of a sudden White's cluster of pieces in the centre are in trouble} 27. Qc3 Ne6 $1 28. Nxe7 $2 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '?!'} ({White can save material with} 28. Nb4 Bb7 29. Nbd3 Nxd4 $17 {when he only loses the bishop pair.} (29... Nxe5 30. Nxe5 Nxd4 31. Qxd4 b4 32. Kf2 Qc3 $19)) 28... Qb7 $1 $19 {White unexpectedly loses a piece by force. The newly minted super-GM eventually converts. Petronijevic,Zoran: '!' White unexpectedly loses a piece by force. The newly minted super-GM eventually converts.} 29. f4 (29. Nxd5 Qxd5 30. Bxa7 Bxe5 31. Qd3 Bd4+ 32. Bxd4 Nxd4 $19) 29... Nxe5 30. Nxd5 Nxd4 31. e4 Nec6 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '-+'} (31... Ng4 $5 $19) 32. Kh1 Ne7 33. Qc7 Qxc7 34. Nxc7 b4 35. Bc4 Kg8 36. Kg2 g5 37. Kf2 Ng6 38. Nd5 a5 39. e5 Kf8 (39... gxf4 40. gxf4 Nh4) 40. Ke3 Nc6 41. Ke4 h5 42. Bb5 Nce7 43. Nb6 gxf4 44. Nd7+ (44. gxf4 f5+) 44... Kg8 45. gxf4 Nf8 46. Nc5 Ne6 47. Nd3 (47. Nxe6 fxe6 48. Bc4 Kf7) 47... Bh6 48. h4 Kg7 49. Bc4 Kg6 50. Bxe6 fxe6 51. Nc5 Kf7 52. Nb7 Nd5 53. Nd6+ Ke7 54. f5 Nc3+ 55. Kd3 Bf4 (55... Nxa2) 56. f6+ Kd7 57. Kd4 Bg3 58. Nb7 Bf2+ 59. Kd3 Nxa2 60. Nxa5 Bxh4 61. Nb7 0-1


