{[%evp 9,111,9,12,6,5,-4,-1,-6,-6,-7,1,-10,-2,-1,1,5,8,0,80,77,107,78,109,123,134,124,131,110,121,106,138,130,129,129,108,78,257,142,155,62,64,62,65,52,152,126,123,146,137,128,140,119,162,135,137,110,112,78,72,77,83,78,78,59,56,46,46,61,103,79,100,78,121,88,207,200,262,260,313,314,350,394,523,503,582,589,708,536,535,545,539,499,608,611,591,573,754,691,692,678,748,734,861,826] A13: English Opening: 1...e6 Nogueiras,J: 'Inf 34/12'} 1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 e6 3. g3 dxc4 4. Qa4+ Bd7 5. Qxc4 c5 6. Bg2 Bc6 7. b3 Be7 8. Bb2 {The position is equal.} Nf6 9. O-O O-O 10. d3 {[%cal Bd2d3,Bd3d4][%mdl 32]} Nbd7 11. Nbd2 Rc8 12. e4 $146 (12. Rac1 Qa5 13. Qc2 Rfd8 14. Qb1 Qa6 15. Rfe1 b6 16. e4 Nf8 17. Nc4 b5 18. Nce5 Be8 19. Qa1 Ng6 20. Rc2 Bf8 21. Rec1 Nxe5 22. Nxe5 Nd7 23. Ng4 f6 24. Bf3 Be7 25. h4 {½-½ Kortschnoj,V-Nogueiras Santiago,J (ol) 34/12 Luzern 1982}) (12. Rfd1 b5 13. Qc1 Nb6 14. Ne5 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Nfd7 16. Ng4 Nf6 17. Nxf6+ Bxf6 18. Bxf6 Qxf6 19. Qa3 Qe7 20. Rac1 f5 21. Qa6 Qd7 22. Nf3 f4 23. Rd2 fxg3 24. hxg3 Rf5 25. a4 bxa4 26. bxa4 Rcf8 {½-½ Sahidi,S (2474)-Berend,E (2219) Olympiad-45 Budapest 2024 (5.29)}) ({RR} 12. Rac1 Qa5 13. Qc2 Rfd8 14. Qb1 Qa6 15. Rfe1 b6 16. e4 Nf8 17. Nc4 b5 18. Nce5 Be8 19. Qa1 Ng6 20. Rc2 Bf8 21. Rec1 Nxe5 22. Nxe5 Nd7 23. Ng4 f6 24. Bf3 Be7 25. h4 {½-½ (25) Kortschnoj,V (2645)-Nogueiras Santiago,J (2495) Luzern 1982}) ({RR} 12. Qc2 b5 13. Rac1 Qb6 14. Qb1 Rfd8 15. Qa1 Ne8 16. Rc2 Bf6 17. Rfc1 Bxb2 18. Qxb2 Nef6 19. h3 h6 20. Ne5 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Rc7 22. Ndf3 Rdc8 23. Nxd7 {½-½ (23) Movsesian,S (2705)-Grachev,B (2672) Sibenik 2012}) 12... Ng4 13. h3 Bf6 {[%eval 80,20]} (13... b5 $11 {[%eval 0,20]} 14. Qc1 Ngf6) 14. d4 $1 $16 Nh6 15. Qe2 Nb6 {[%cal Rc5d4]} 16. Qe3 cxd4 17. Nxd4 Bxd4 18. Bxd4 (18. Qxd4 f6 $16) 18... f5 19. Bc5 Rf7 20. Bxb6 axb6 21. Nc4 $1 {[%cal Bd2c4,Bc4d6,Bd6f5][%mdl 32]} fxe4 22. Rad1 (22. Nxb6 Nf5 23. Qc5 Rcc7 $17) 22... Qf8 {[%eval 257,22]} (22... Qf6 $16 {[%eval 78,23] was worth a try.}) 23. Bxe4 {[%eval 142,20]} (23. Ne5 $18 {[%eval 257,22]}) 23... Nf5 24. Bxf5 {[%eval 62,23]} (24. Qxb6 Bxe4 25. Ne5 Re7 $19) ({White should try} 24. Qe2 $1 $16 {[%eval 155,22]}) 24... exf5 $14 25. Nd6 Re7 $1 26. Qg5 h6 {[%eval 152,26]} (26... Ra8 $14 {[%eval 52,22]}) 27. Qg6 $1 $16 Be8 28. Qxf5 {White is much more active.} Qxf5 29. Nxf5 Re5 30. Nd4 Ra5 {[%eval 162,22]} (30... b5 $16 {[%eval 119,20]}) 31. Rd2 $18 Rca8 32. Re1 Bd7 33. a4 Rd5 34. g4 h5 35. f3 hxg4 36. fxg4 b5 37. axb5 Bxb5 38. Red1 {Black is on the road to losing.} Ra3 {[%eval 103,23]} (38... Re5 $14 {[%eval 61,25] deserves consideration.}) 39. Kf2 $16 Be8 40. h4 Bf7 {[%eval 121,23] [#]} ({Black should play} 40... Rd7 {[%eval 78,23]}) 41. b4 $1 Rd6 {[%eval 207,25]} (41... g6 $16 {[%eval 88,22]}) 42. Nf3 Rxd2+ 43. Rxd2 $18 {[%mdl 4096] Endgame KRB-KRN. White is a pawn up.} (43. Nxd2 Rd3 $11) 43... Kf8 44. Kg3 Rb3 {[%cal Of7e8]} 45. Rd4 b5 46. Kf4 {White is clearly winning.} Bc4 {[#]} 47. Ne5 $1 Kg8 48. Nc6 ({And not} 48. Nxc4 Rxb4 49. h5 (49. Rd8+ Kh7 $11) 49... Rxc4 50. Rxc4 bxc4 $11) 48... Kh7 49. h5 Rb1 50. Rd7 Be2 51. Kg5 Rg1 52. Ne5 Rh1 53. Re7 Bd1 54. Ng6 {Intending Re8 and mate.} Bb3 55. Nh4 {h6 would now be deadly.} Kh8 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.14 (very precise) /Black=0.32} 56. Nf5 1-0


