{[%evp 14,73,-11,-11,1,-3,0,-1,3,2,-1,-9,9,1,9,17,9,6,11,1,3,-1,1,-5,1,-12,-23,-34,-23,-37,1,-9,-1,-2,1,-1,-1,-17,1,-1,31,1,13,18,45,-1,36,41,54,86,310,321,330,299,1052,1049,1048,879,880,857,1012,596] A04: Unusual lines after 1 Nf3 and King's Indian Attack} 1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O Nc6 5. c3 e5 6. e4 Nge7 7. d3 O-O 8. a3 a5 9. a4 d5 (9... d6 10. Na3 h6 11. Nd2 Be6 12. Ndc4 Kh7 13. Re1 b6 14. Qb3 Rb8 15. f4 d5 16. exd5 Bxd5 17. Qd1 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Qd5+ 19. Qf3 Qxf3+ 20. Kxf3 Rfd8 21. fxe5 Rxd3+ {½-½ Gharamian,T (2663)-Riff,J (2467) Metz op 31th 2013 (3)}) 10. Na3 d4 $146 {The position is equal.} (10... h6 11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Re1 (12. Qb3 Be6 13. Qxb7 Nce7 14. Nc4 Rb8 15. Qa6 e4 16. Nfd2 exd3 17. Re1 Qc8 18. Qxc8 Rfxc8 {Vestly,J-Aman Hambleton  Ian Zhao AOCT N233B corr 1990}) 12... b6 13. Nc4 Re8 14. Bd2 Ra7 15. Qb3 Rd7 {A 05/08-N,N  2000}) ({RR} 10... h6 11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Qb3 Nde7 13. Be3 Be6 14. Nc4 Qxd3 15. Nfd2 Bd5 16. Bxd5 Qxd5 17. Nb6 Qxb3 18. Nxb3 Rad8 19. Rfd1 Rxd1+ 20. Rxd1 Rd8 21. Rxd8+ Nxd8 22. Nxa5 Nec6 23. Nxc6 Nxc6 24. Bxc5 Bf8 25. Nd7 {Amin,B (2635)-Moiseenko,A (2707) Dubai 2014 1-0 (40)}) 11. cxd4 cxd4 12. Nc4 Rb8 $146 ({RR} 12... Be6 13. b3 f6 14. Bd2 Nb4 15. Bxb4 axb4 16. Qd2 Nc6 17. Nh4 Kh8 18. Kh1 Rb8 19. f4 Bh6 20. Qe2 Qc7 21. f5 Bxc4 22. bxc4 g5 23. Nf3 g4 24. Nh4 Rg8 25. Rfb1 Qg7 26. Bf1 Qg5 27. Ra2 {Siebert,L (2263)-Wyrwich,M (2084) Germany 1999 ½-½}) 13. b3 b5 14. axb5 Rxb5 15. Ba3 Nb4 16. Bxb4 axb4 17. Nfd2 Be6 18. Ra6 Bc8 19. Ra7 Nc6 20. Ra8 {[%cal Og2h3]} Qc7 21. f4 exf4 {[%eval 1,19]} (21... Be6 $15 {[%eval -37,18] might be stronger.} 22. Rxf8+ Bxf8) 22. gxf4 $11 Be6 23. Rxf8+ Bxf8 {[%cal Bg7f8,Bf8e7,Be7g5][%mdl 32]} 24. Qf3 Na5 25. e5 $1 Be7 26. Qg3 f5 27. h4 {[%cal Bh2h4,Bh4h5][%mdl 32]} Qd8 28. h5 Kg7 29. Bf3 {[%eval -1,20]} (29. Kh1 $14 {[%eval 45,17]}) 29... g5 {[%eval 36,18]} (29... Nxc4 $11 {[%eval -1,20]} 30. Nxc4 Bxc4 31. dxc4 Ra5) 30. fxg5 $14 {Nd6 would now be deadly.} Bxg5 {[#]} 31. Be4 $1 {A mistake that costs the game.} fxe4 $2 {[%eval 310,21]} (31... Kh8 $16 {[%eval 86,19] might work better.}) (31... f4 32. Rxf4) 32. Nxe4 $18 ({And not} 32. Rf6 Rxe5 33. Nxe4 Nxc4 34. Rxe6 Rxe4 (34... Rxe6 35. Nxg5 $15) 35. dxe4 Kf7 $17) 32... Kh6 {[#] ...Nxc4 is the strong threat.} 33. Ncd6 {Excellent horsemanship.} Rb6 $2 {[%eval 1052,23] [#]} (33... Bh4 {[%eval 299,19]} 34. Qf4+ Bg5 35. Qxg5+ Qxg5+ 36. Nxg5 Kxg5 37. Nxb5 Nxb3) 34. Rf6+ $1 {[%mdl 512] White is clearly winning.} Bxf6 35. exf6 Qg8 {[#] Dodges Qg5+} 36. Nf5+ $1 {[%mdl 576] Deflection, Promotion} Bxf5 {Weighted Error Value: White=0.06 (flawless) /Black=0.40} 37. Qxg8 1-0


