{[%evp 0,15,19,38,40,6,20,22,15,-5,48,23,24,22,49,0,19,32] Our team got double White in the first two matches which was lucky for me and I was looking forward to this game as I liked Parham's uncompromising style.} 1. e4 {Sam Collins Adhiban, Baskaran Sam Collins: 'Adhiban,Baskaran'} c5 {I didn't really prepare for this much and hence decided to bail out with} 2. Nf3 $5 {One of the boring lines ever to be invented...} e6 {He had played this once before in the only ever game where he faced Alapin.} 3. d4 {I gave one last chance to Parham to transpose with ...Nf6!} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 {Again this was the very last time I was indirectly requesting to transpose back to Alapin.} Qc7 {As Naka would say "It is what it is!"} 6. Be3 {Now we are in some French Tarrasch type structures.} a6 7. Be2 b5 8. Nxc6 Qxc6 9. Bf3 {Sam Collins: 'Of course this position could arise from a French Tarrasch (1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.Nd2 c5 4.exd5 exd5 5.Ngf3 Nc6 6.Bb5 Bd6 7.dxc5 Bxc5 8.0-0 Ne7) if White chose the non-critical 9.c3. That said, c3 is a useful move and the character of the position (an IQP where Black has reasonable chances to equalise with precise play) is the same in both cases.'} Bb7 10. O-O Qc7 11. Re1 Bd6 12. g3 Ne7 13. Qd2 Rd8 14. Rad1 Be5 15. Bg2 {Sam Collins: 'Black is, of course, very comfortable here.' A nice transformation and also now Black is clearly behind in development.} Bxc3 $146 ({RR} 15... O-O 16. f4 Bxc3 17. Qxc3 Qxc3 18. bxc3 Bc6 19. Bc5 Rfe8 20. Rd3 Rc8 21. Bb4 f6 22. Red1 Rc7 23. Kf2 Kf7 24. Bd6 Rb7 25. Bf3 Nc8 26. Bc5 Rd8 27. Ke3 Rc7 28. Bd6 Nxd6 29. Rxd6 Ke7 30. R1d3 {Sadhwani,R (2246)-Ivanisevic,I (2648) Sitges 2016 0-1 (96)}) 16. bxc3 d5 17. Bf4 Qc8 18. e5 $5 {I was quite happy to play the manoeuvring game but...at the same time I wanted to exploit my lead in development hence decided to open up the position!} Rd7 19. h4 {Sam Collins: 'Now Black must play precisely to neutralise White's lead in development.' Bring all your pieces to the party!} Rc7 20. Bg5 h6 21. Bxe7 $5 Kxe7 {Sam Collins: '?!' A huge error missing my next move...} 22. Re3 $1 Rd8 {Sam Collins: '?'} 23. Qd3 {At first I wasn't happy to allow the rook to get back into the game but then saw that the idea of Ne3-d5 was very strong.} d4 (23... Rc4) 24. cxd4 {Sam Collins: '+-' Sam Collins: 'The attacking ratio on the kingside is intimidating. The Iranian talent grabs a pawn so as to have something to suffer for.'} Bxg2 25. Kxg2 Rxc2 26. Qh7 Qc6+ 27. Rf3 Rc3 {Sam Collins: 'Adhiban,Baskaran'} 28. Rdd3 {Sam Collins: '1-0 (31) Adhiban,B (2683)-Maghsoodloo,P (2673) Astana 2019 CBM 189 [Adhiban,Baskaran]'} Rxd3 29. Qxd3 {This looked cleanest.} g6 30. Qe3 Rd7 31. Qxh6 {Generally a blow at the top is enough for match victory but it wasn't one of those days...} Kd8 {Sam Collins: 'Adhiban,Baskaran' was my other idea.} 32. Qf8+ Kc7 {also winning.} 33. g4 Qe4 1-0


