{D24: Queen's Gambit Accepted: 3 Nf3 Nf6 4 Nc3} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 d5 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. e4 b5 6. e5 Nd5 7. Nxb5 Nb6 8. Be2 {White is slightly better.} Nc6 9. O-O Be7 10. Qd2 O-O 11. Qf4 Rb8 12. Qg3 {Threatening Bh6.} Kh8 $1 13. Rd1 Nb4 14. Nc3 (14. Nxa7 Bd7 15. b3 Ra8 16. bxc4 Rxa7 $17) 14... Bb7 15. Rb1 ({RR} 15. h4 Nc2 16. Rb1 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 Nxd4 18. Bg5 c5 19. Ne4 f6 20. Bf4 f5 21. Ng5 Bxg5 22. hxg5 Nd5 23. Bd2 f4 24. Qg4 Nxf3+ 25. Qxf3 Qxg5 26. Re1 Rf5 27. Re4 Qh4 28. g3 fxg3 29. Rxh4 Rxf3 {Tanriverdi,E (2371)-Maghsoodloo,P (2707) Chess.com INT 2023 0-1}) ({RR} 15. h4 Nc2 16. Rb1 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 Nxd4 18. Bg5 c5 19. Ne4 f6 20. Bf4 f5 21. Ng5 Bxg5 22. hxg5 Nd5 23. Bd2 f4 24. Qg4 Nxf3+ 25. Qxf3 Qxg5 26. Re1 Rf5 27. Re4 Qh4 28. g3 fxg3 29. Rxh4 Rxf3 {Tanriverdi,E (2371)-Maghsoodloo,P (2707) Chess.com INT 2023 0-1}) 15... N4d5 16. Ne4 $146 ({RR} 16. Bd2 Nxc3 17. Bxc3 Bd5 18. b3 Be4 19. Ra1 Nd5 {6) Vienna - Main Line 5.e4 b5-Vienna − 5.e4 b5 6.e5 Nd5 7} 20. Be1 c3 21. Bd3 Bxd3 22. Rxd3 Ba3 23. Bxc3 Nxc3 24. Rxc3 Bb2 25. Rac1 c5 26. Rxc5 Bxc1 27. Rxc1 Qa5 28. h4 Qxa2 29. Qf4 Qxb3 30. Ng5 h6 {Goganov,A (2594)-Nepomniachtchi,I (2784) Moscow 2020 0-1 (46)}) ({RR} 16. Bd2 Nxc3 17. Bxc3 Bd5 18. b3 Be4 19. Ra1 Nd5 20. Be1 c3 21. Bd3 Bxd3 22. Rxd3 Ba3 23. Bxc3 Nxc3 24. Rxc3 Bb2 25. Rac1 c5 26. Rxc5 Bxc1 27. Rxc1 Qa5 28. h4 Qxa2 29. Qf4 Qxb3 30. Ng5 h6 {Goganov,A (2594)-Nepomniachtchi,I (2784) Moscow 2020 0-1 (46)}) 16... f5 {[%eval 73,18]} (16... Ne3 $11 {[%eval -13,20]} 17. Bxe3 Bxe4) 17. exf6 {[%eval 21,18]} (17. Nc5 $1 $16 {[%eval 73,18][%cal Rc5e6]} Qc8 18. Ng5) 17... gxf6 $11 18. Nc5 Bc8 19. Ne4 Qe8 {Threatening ...e5!.} 20. Bd2 {[%eval -63,21]} (20. Qh4 $11 {[%eval -6,18]}) 20... Rg8 21. Qh4 e5 22. h3 {[%eval -105,20] Against Rg4} (22. dxe5 $2 Rg4 23. exf6 Rxh4 24. Nxh4 Bxf6 (24... Nxf6 $2 25. Bc3 $19) 25. Nxf6 Qxe2 $19) ({White should try} 22. Ng3 $1 $15 {[%eval -52,20]}) 22... Qg6 $17 23. Ng3 {[%eval -195,21] [#]} (23. Bf1 $17 {[%eval -95,21]} exd4 24. Re1 (24. Nxd4 $2 f5 $19)) 23... Bf5 $1 $36 {Black is in control.} 24. Rbc1 {[%eval -252,20]} (24. Ra1 $17 {[%eval -152,22]} e4 25. Ne1) 24... e4 25. Nh2 {[#]} e3 $1 26. Be1 Bd3 27. Qg4 Bxe2 28. Nxe2 Na4 29. Qf3 {[%eval -343,21]} (29. Qxg6 $142 {[%eval -194,20]} Rxg6 30. Rc2) 29... Nxb2 (29... Rxb2 30. Qxd5 Rxe2 31. Ng4 $17) 30. Qxd5 Nxd1 31. Rxd1 Qc2 $1 32. Nc3 exf2+ {Overworked Piece} 33. Bxf2 {Threatens to win with Qf3.} Qxc3 34. Ng4 Qc2 35. Re1 Bb4 {[%eval -128,19]} (35... Rb1 $19 {[%eval -365,19] has better winning chances.} 36. Qe6 Rxe1+ 37. Bxe1 Re8) 36. Bh4 $17 Rbf8 ({And not} 36... Qxa2 37. Bxf6+ Rg7 38. Bxg7+ Kxg7 39. Qg5+ Kh8 40. Qf6+ Kg8 41. Nh6#) 37. Bxf6+ {[#]} Rxf6 $1 38. Nxf6 Rxg2+ 39. Qxg2 Qxg2+ 40. Kxg2 Bxe1 {Endgame KB-KN. Black is a pawn up.} 41. Nd5 {[%eval -242,25]} (41. Kf1 {[%eval -177,27] might work better.} Bc3 42. Nd5 Bxd4 43. Ke2) 41... c3 $19 42. Nb4 {[#]} Bh4 $1 43. Kf3 Be7 44. Nc2 Kg7 45. Ne3 {[%eval -383,26]} (45. Ke3 $142 {[%eval -243,24]} Kg6 46. Kd3) 45... Kg6 46. Ke4 Kg5 47. Kf3 Kh4 48. Kg2 Bg5 49. Nc2 Bf6 50. Kh2 Be7 51. Kg2 c5 52. dxc5 Bxc5 53. Ne1 Bb6 54. Nc2 Kg5 55. Kf3 Kf5 56. Nb4 Bc5 57. Nc2 Ke5 58. Na1 Be7 59. Nc2 Bg5 60. Nb4 Kd4 61. Ke2 Ke4 62. Nc2 {[%eval -809,29]} (62. a3 $142 {[%eval -474,27]} Be7 63. Nc2) 62... Bf4 63. Nb4 Be3 64. Nc2 {[%eval -836,30]} (64. Kd1 $142 {[%eval -400,27]} Bc5 65. Nc6) 64... Bb6 65. Nb4 Be3 $2 {[%eval 1,23]} (65... Ba5 $19 {[%eval -755,27]} 66. Nc2 h5) {White does not recover from this.} 66. Nc2 $11 Bc5 67. Ne1 {[%eval -730,31]} (67. a4 $142 {[%eval -436,25]}) 67... Bb6 $19 68. Nd3 h5 69. Nb4 Bc5 70. Nd3 Be3 71. Nb4 Bb6 72. Nd3 c2 73. Kd2 Kf3 74. Kxc2 Kg3 75. Kd2 Kxh3 76. Ke2 Kg3 77. Kf1 h4 {( -> ...h3)} 78. Nc1 h3 79. Ne2+ Kf3 {( -> ...h2)} 80. Ng1+ Kg4 {[%eval -973,28]} 81. Ne2 a5 {( -> ...Be3)} 82. a4 Kf3 {[%eval -1032,25]} (82... Ba7 $142 {[%eval -32723,25]} 83. Nc3 Kf3 84. Nd1 Kg3 85. Nc3 h2 86. Ne4+ Kf4 87. Kg2 Kxe4 88. Kxh2 Kd3 89. Kg3 Kc3 90. Kg4 Kb4 91. Kg5 Kxa4 92. Kf5 Kb3 93. Kg4 a4 94. Kh4 a3 (